nt to &quot;1&gt; / dev / null&quot;</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Thus,&gt; / dev / null 2&gt; &amp; 1 can also be written as &quot;1&gt; / dev / null 2&gt; &amp; 1&quot;</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Then the execution of this statement in the title is: <br /> 1&gt; / dev / null: first that the standard output redirected to a null device file, which is not output any information to the terminal, it means do not display any information. <br /> 2 &quot;&amp; 1: Then, the standard error output redirected to standard output, because before the standard output has been redirected to a null device file, so the standard error output are redirected to a null device file.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">That clear to you, we understand, are you!</font> </p><p> <font color=\"#ff6600\" face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Under such a contrast with the way the benefits of telling!</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">The most common methods are:</font> </p><p> <font color=\"#ff0000\" face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">command&gt; file 2&gt; file with the command&gt; file 2&gt; &amp; 1</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">What is different place?</font> </p><p><br /> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">First command&gt; file 2&gt; file means that the standards produced by the command output, and errors in the information to the file. Command&gt; file 2&gt; file that is written, stdout and stderr are sent directly to the file in, file will be opened twice, so stdout and stderr will overwrite each other so very used to write both FD1 and FD2 at the same time to seize the file in the pipeline. <br /> The command&gt; file 2&gt; &amp; 1 This command will be sent directly to the stdout file, stderr inherited FD1 pipe, and then was sent to file, time, file is opened only once, only use a pipe FD1, it includes the contents of stdout and stderr. <br /> From the IO efficiency, the efficiency of a command before the back of a command than less efficient, so when writing shell scripts, more time, we will command&gt; file 2&gt; &amp; 1 this writing.</font> </p></div> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>','Today, a technology in their own group so they were asked a question, so he explained a bit popular, to be a record, we look to explain it clearly!shell may often see:> / dev / null 2> & 1The results can command%> to define the output in the form ofDecomposition of this combination: \"> / dev / null...'),(43,'Linux','linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0610/201.html','http://www.ixdba.net','configuration and tuning tomcat cluster implementation plan','configuration_and_tuning_tomcat_cluster_implementation_plan','2010-06-10','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <font size=\"2\"><strong>First, the operating system tuning <br /></strong> Optimization of the operating system, it is possible the increase of memory capacity can be used to improve the CPU frequency, to ensure the file system read and write speed and so on. After pressure testing and certification, in the case of many concurrent connections, CPU processing power is stronger, the system runs faster. . <br /> SceneÃ£Â€Â‘ Ã£Â€Âapply to any project. <br /> <strong>Second, Java Virtual Machine tuning</strong> &lt;br /&gt; should choose SUN\'s JVM, the premise of meeting the needs of the project as far as selection of a higher version of JVM, generally high version of the product than the low speed and efficiency will be improved versions of . <br /> JDK1.4 JDK1.3 performance improvement than the nearly 10% -20%, JDK1.5 JDK1.4 than 25% -75% performance increase. <br /> Therefore, the situation on the high performance requirements recommended JDK1.6. <br /> SceneÃ£Â€Â‘ Ã£Â€Âapply to any project. <br /> <strong>Third, Apache Integration <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/web/tomcat/\">Tomcat</a></u></strong> <br /> HTTP Web server dedicated to handling requests, the application server is provided through a number of protocols for the application business logic. While the Tomcat web server can also be made, but the deal\'s not as fast as static html Apache, and web server functionality as far as Apache, so to integrate Apache and Tomcat, Jsp will feature some of html and a clear division of labor, Jsp Tomcat parts to deal only with the other by the Apache, IIS and other web servers to handle, thus greatly improving the operating efficiency of Tomcat. <br /> If a project makes extensive use of static pages, a large number of pictures and have a greater number of visits, integrated Apache Tomcat recommended way to improve overall system performance. <br /> The integration of Apache and Tomcat, there are three ways, namely, JK, http_proxy and ajp_proxy. Where JK is the most common way of approach, JK itself has two versions 1 and 2, respectively, present a new version is 1.2.8, and version 2 already obsolete. http_proxy is to use Apache\'s mod_proxy module is built using agent technology to connect to Tomcat. Ajp_proxy connection with the http_proxy the same way as a matter of fact, all the functions provided by the mod_proxy. Just need to configure the http:// into ajp: / /, while the connection is where Tomcat\'s AJP Connector port. <br /> JK\'s connections with respect to the latter two is relatively simple in configuration, flexibility, a little also favorably. But in terms of stability of not JK proven so, so JK\'s connection is recommended. <br /> Apache + JK + Tomcat configuration: <br /> The two configuration files used are: httpd.conf and mod_jk.conf. Which is the Apache server\'s httpd.conf configuration file to load the JK module, and specify the JK configuration file information. mod_jk.conf is connected to the Tomcat server definition file. <br /> Ã£Â€Â‘ Ã£Â€ÂDeployment steps <br /> 1. Installing Apache Server <br /> 2. Deployment Tomcat <br /> 3. Mod_jk.so copy the modules directory <br /> 4. Modify httpd.conf and mod_jk.conf <br /> Ã£Â€ÂÃ£Â€Â‘ Large number of scenarios for the applications use a static page. <br /> <strong>Fourth, Apache and Tomcat clustering</strong> &lt;br /&gt; demanding for concurrent systems, we need to take a balanced approach to share the load Tomcat server stress. Load balancing to achieve about four: the first is through DNS, but only the realization of a simple rotation distribution, can not deal with failure; the second is based on MS IIS, windows 2003 server itself with the load balancing services; the third is the hardware approach through the switch load balancing function or special equipment to achieve; the fourth is the software of the way through a load balancing server, install the software above. Done using Apache Httpd Server load balancer, Tomcat Tomcat cluster nodes can be done using the fourth approach, more flexible this way, the cost is relatively low, the other big advantage is that applications and servers according to the situation some flexibility in configuration. So it is Apache + Tomcat clustering for load balancing. <br /> Tomcat clusters can be used to play the greatest degree of performance of the server, the server can be configured to deploy a higher number of Tomcat, can also be deployed on multiple servers are Tomcat, Apache and Tomcat JK integrated way or manner. After verification, the system response to a large amount of users using the terms, Apache +3 Tomccat cluster&gt; Apache +2 Tomcat cluster&gt; Apache integrating Tomcat&gt; single Tomcat. And using Apache + Tomcat cluster deployment and more, if a Tomcat Chuxian down, the system can continue to use, so the performance of the hardware system is superior enough to the case, you need to maximize the performance of the software can be used to increase Tomcat cluster approach. <br /> Apache + Tomcat to use the cluster configuration file must have httpd.conf, mod_jk.conf, workers.properties. JK mod_jk.conf which is the configuration information, including the path of JK, workers.properties Tomcat server configuration file is the connection definition file. <br /> Apache need to adjust the operating parameters, so as to build a network environment suitable for the corresponding web services. Which may be the optimal allocation is as follows: <br /> 1. Set MPM (Multi Processing Modules Multi-Processing Modules). ThreadPerChild, this parameter is used to set the number of threads per process in Windows environment, the default value is 64, maximum is 1920, among the recommendations is set to 100-500, then the value of high performance servers larger, whereas smaller. MaxRequestPerChild that each child process to handle the maximum number of requests. Greater the value of this parameter depends on the server\'s memory, if memory is relatively large, then the parameters can be set to large, or to set a smaller value, the proposed value is 3000. <br /> 2. Close DNS and name resolution</font> <wbr /><wbr /> <font size=\"2\">HostnameLookups off <br /> 3. Open UseCanonicalName module UseCanonicalName on <br /> 4. Close extra modules in general, need to load the module, mod_include.so, mod_autoindex.so, mod_access.so, mod_auth.so. <br /> 5. Open KeepAlive support <br /> KeepAlive on, KeepAliveTimeout 15 MaxKeepAliveRequests 1000 <br /></font> <wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /> <font size=\"2\">Based on actual experience, by the way Apache and Tomcat clustering to improve system performance of the effect is very obvious, this approach can maximize the use of hardware resources, through multiple treatment to share a single Tomcat when Tomcat pressure. <br /> Ã£Â€Â‘ Ã£Â€ÂDeployment steps <br /> 1. Installing Apache Server <br /> 2. To deploy Tomcat cluster, that is more than the same Tomcat. <br /> 3. Mod_jk.so copy the modules directory <br /> 4. Modify httpd.conf, mod_jk.conf and workers.properties <br /> Ã£Â€ÂÃ£Â€Â‘ Concurrent users for the amount of the scene and the relatively high number of users online using the system. <br /> <strong>V., Tomcat itself Optimization</strong> <br /> <strong>1. JVM tuning parameters:-Xms</strong> &lt;size&gt; that initialize JVM heap size,-Xmx &lt;size&gt; that the maximum JVM heap. The size of these two values is generally based on the need for setting. When the application requires the maximum heap memory beyond the virtual machine will be prompted when the memory overflow and cause applications to crash. It is generally recommended the maximum heap is set to the maximum available memory to 80%. In catalina.bat, set JAVA_OPTS = \'-Xms256m-Xmx512m\', said initialization memory 256MB, you can use the maximum memory 512MB. <br /> <strong>2. Disable DNS query</strong> &lt;br /&gt; When the web application to client information to be recorded, it will record the client\'s IP address or domain name server looks through the machine names are converted to IP addresses. DNS queries need to occupy the network, and including the possibility of a lot of very far from the server or the server does not work up the process to obtain the corresponding IP, which will consume some time. In order to eliminate the performance impact of DNS queries that we can turn off DNS queries, way is to modify the server.xml file enableLookups parameter values: <br /> Tomcat4 <br /><br /> &lt;Connector className = &quot;org.apache.coyote.tomcat4.CoyoteConnector&quot; port = &quot;80&quot; minProcessors = &quot;5&quot; maxProcessors = &quot;75&quot; enableLookups = &quot;false&quot; redirectPort = &quot;8443&quot; acceptCount = &quot;100&quot; debug = &quot;0&quot; connectionTimeout = &quot;20000&quot; useURIValidationHack = &quot;false&quot; disableUploadTimeout = &quot;true&quot; /&gt; <br /><br /> Tomcat5 <br /><br /> &lt;Connector port = &quot;80&quot; maxThreads = &quot;150&quot; minSpareThreads = &quot;25&quot; maxSpareThreads = &quot;75&quot; enableLookups = &quot;false&quot; redirectPort = &quot;8443&quot; acceptCount = &quot;100&quot; debug = &quot;0&quot; connectionTimeout = &quot;20000&quot; disableUploadTimeout = &quot; true &quot;/&gt;</font> </p><p><br /> <strong>3.</strong> &lt;br /&gt; By <strong>adjusting the number of threads</strong> the application\'s connector (Connector) control the parameters of performance is to create a number of threads to process the request. Tomcat uses a thread pool to accelerate response time to process the request. In the Java runtime in the thread is the path in a program independent of the other threads of control that can operate independently of the code. They share the same address space. To help programmers write multi-threaded CPU maximum utilization of the efficient processes that maintain a minimum idle time to accept more requests. <br /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /> Tomcat4 can minProcessors and maxProcessors by modifying the values to control the number of threads. These values after the installation has been set as the default and is sufficient to use, but instead as the site of a large expansion of these values. minProcessors created when the server starts processing the request should be sufficient number of threads dealing with a small amount of load. That is, if the day occurs only 5 times per second click event, and the task of processing each request takes 1 second, then to 5 pre-set number of threads is sufficient. But the traffic on your site will need to set a larger large number of threads, specify the value for the parameter maxProcessors. maxProcessors\'s value is also an upper limit should not prevent the flow of control (or malicious service attacks), which leads to memory beyond the size of the virtual machine to use. If you want to increase the number of concurrent connections, should also increase these two parameters. web server to allow the maximum number of connections is also subject to the operating system kernel parameters, usually Windows is about 2000, Linux is about 1000. <br /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /> In Tomcat5 were adjusted for these parameters, see the following attributes: <br /> maxThreads <wbr /><wbr /><wbr /> Tomcat using threads to handle each request received. This value represents the Tomcat to create the largest number of threads. <br /> acceptCount <wbr /><wbr /><wbr /> Specify when all that can be used to process the request threads are used, you can put the number of processing requests in the queue, more than the number of requests will be processed. <br /> connnectionTimeout <wbr /><wbr /><wbr /> Network connection timeout, unit: milliseconds. Set to 0 to never time out, so set up a hidden danger. Usually set to 30000 milliseconds. <br /> minSpareThreads <wbr /><wbr /><wbr /> Tomcat initialization the number of threads created. <br /><br /> maxSpareThreads <wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /> Once you create a thread more than this value, Tomcat will no longer need to close the socket threads. <br /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /> The best way is to set a few more tests and to observe the response time and memory usage. On different machines, operating system or virtual machines may be combined in different circumstances, but not all of the web site\'s traffic is the same, so there is no one size fits all solution to determine the value of the number of threads. </p><p><br /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /> Tomcat uses a thread pool to accelerate response time to process the request. In the Java runtime in the thread is the path in a program with <br /><wbr /> It is independent of the control threads can run independently of the code. They share the same address space. To help programmers write multi-threaded CPU most <br /><wbr /> Great utilization of efficient processes that maintain a minimum idle time to accept more requests. <br /><wbr /> Examples are as follows: <br /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /> &lt;Connector port = &quot;80&quot; protocol = &quot;HTTP/1.1&quot; <br /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /> maxThreads = &quot;600&quot; maximum number of threads running <wbr /><wbr /><br /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /> minSpareThreads = &quot;100&quot; Initialize the number of threads created <br /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /> maxSpareThreads = &quot;500&quot; <br /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /> Maximum number of threads can be created, the thread more than once to create this value, Tomcat will no longer need to close the socket threads. <br /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /> acceptCount = &quot;700&quot; specify when all available threads to process the request have been used <br /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /> Treatment can be placed in the number of requests in the queue, more than the number of requests will be processed <br /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /> connectionTimeout = &quot;20000&quot; <br /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /> enableLookups = &quot;false&quot; <br /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /> redirectPort = &quot;8443&quot; /&gt; <br /> <strong>VI, APR library use <br /></strong> APR libraries used in Tomcat, is actually used in the Tomcat JNI way to read the file, and network transmission. Tomcat can greatly enhance the processing performance of the static file, and if you use HTTPS if transmitted, can also enhance the performance of SSL processing. <br /> Usually in Windows, you can directly download the compiled binary version of the dll library to enable the Tomcat APR, is generally recommended tcnative-1.dll copy library file to Tomcat\'s bin directory. In Linux, you can extract and install the bin directory directly under the tomcat_native.tar.gz file before compiling to ensure that the apr library is installed. <br /> How can we determine whether you have enabled Tomcat APR library? Method is to start by looking at Tomcat\'s log: <br /> If you do not enable the APR, the general that there is a startup log: <br /> org.apache.coyote.http11.Http11Protocol start <br /> If you enable the APR, then the log will become this: <br /> org.apache.coyote.http11.Http11AprProtocol start <br /> tcnative-1.dll Download: http://tomcat.heanet.ie/native/ <br /><wbr /><wbr /> <strong>Tuning Summary <br /></strong> <wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /><wbr /> Based on the above analysis, if you want Tomcat to achieve optimal results, first for making the operating system and network resources to achieve optimal and best use of the high version of the JDK. A large number of static pages for the system, using Apache Tomcat integrated manner by the Apache handle static pages, dynamic part of the deal by Tomcat, Tomcat can be a great liberation of processing power. ARP library can be used to improve greatly Tomcat on static file processing capabilities. Concurrent requirement for higher system, the use of Apache Tomcat plus the way the cluster, the load sharing across multiple Tomcat, respectively, and can greatly improve system performance, full use of hardware resources. Tomcat itself also needs to be optimized, including increased memory, such as adjusting the number of concurrent threads. <wbr /></p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>','First, the operating system tuning  Optimization of the operating system, it is possible the increase of memory capacity can be used to improve the CPU frequency, to ensure the file system read and write speed and so on. After pressure testing and certification, in the case of many concurrent...'),(44,'Linux','linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0422/33.html','http://www.ixdba.net','PXE + TFTP + DHCP network automatically boot the installation L','PXE__TFTP__DHCP_network_automatically_boot_the_installation_L','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">His earlier written an article to share with you the next! <br /><br /> <font color=\"#ff0000\">Overview</font> <br /><br /> PXE (preboot execute environment), developed by Intel\'s latest technology, working in the Client / Server network model to support the station through the network from a remote server to download images, and thus support from the network operating system boot process, and its During startup, the terminal requires the server to assign IP addresses, then TFTP (trivial file transfer protocol) or MTFTP (multicast trivial file transfer protocol) protocol to download a boot package to a local memory and executed by the end of this startup software package basic software settings to guide the pre-installed in the server terminal operating system. PXE can boot multiple operating systems, such as: Windows 95/98/2000/xp/2003/vista/2008, linux and so on. <br /><br /> Most direct expression of PXE, the stations in the network environment can save hard drive, but not usually refer to the concept of diskless stations, since the use of the technology in the network mode PC running speed faster than the PC with disk 3 times. Of course, the PC using the PXE is not in the traditional sense TERMINAL terminal, because the PC using the PXE server is not consuming CPU, RAM and other resources, so the server hardware requirements low. <br /> Cloning PXE network is now the most widely used one is the cafe of the diskless technology. The field in a disk in the PXE network maintenance and installation can be the best system to use Internet cafes to install and maintain a unified guidance technology, PXE boot speed and stability are the best! <br /><br /> <font color=\"#ff0000\">A: Installation Environment</font> <br /><br /> A Linux server, linux service, need to install the tftp + dhcp. As a remote installation of network servers. <br /> Client host, which is the need to install the Linux system, the host, the host motherboard must support boot from network. <br /><br /> <font color=\"#ff0000\">II: Installation and Configuration Linux software on a network server to tftp and dhcp</font> <br /><br /> 1: Check for installed tftp <br /> [Root @ webserver html] # rpm-qa tftp * <br /> tftp-server-0.42-3.1.el5.centos <br /> tftp-0.42-3.1.el5.centos <br /> If not, that is not installed, if your system supports yum, direct execution <br /> [Root @ webserver html] # yum install * tftp * <br /> 2: Check whether the service in accordance with the dhcp <br /> [Root @ webserver html] # rpm-qa dhcp * <br /> dhcpv6-client-1.0.10-16.el5 <br /> dhcp-3.0.5-18.el5 <br /> If you do not dhcp, also perform yum install. <br /> [Root @ webserver html] # yum install dhcp * <br /> 3: Configuring tftp service dhcp service (1) configuration tftp service <br /> Tftp is bound by default under the xinetd service, therefore, will want to modify the file to the tftp / etc / xinetd.d to complete, the modified tftp file as follows, where &quot;disable&quot; option from the &quot;yes&quot; is amended as &quot;no&quot;, an increase in the server_args option &quot;-u nobody&quot; parameter, so that any user can access. <br /> [Root @ webserver html] # more / etc / xinetd.d / tftp <br /> # Default: off <br /> # Description: The tftp server serves files using the trivial file transfer \\ <br /> # Protocol. The tftp protocol is often used to boot diskless \\ <br /> # Workstations, download configuration files to network-aware printers, \\ <br /> # And to start the installation process for some operating systems. <br /> service tftp <br /> { <br /> socket_type = dgram <br /> protocol = udp <br /> wait = yes <br /> user = root <br /> server = / usr / sbin / in.tftpd</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">server_args =-u nobody-s / tftpboot <br /> disable = no <br /> per_source = 11 <br /> cps = 100 2 <br /> flags = IPv4 <br /> } <br /> (2) the default configuration dhcp service dhcp configuration file in / etc / dhcpd.Conf, this file defaults to an empty file, so let\'s copy a dhcpd configuration file template file over, then you can modify. <br /> [Root @ webserverhtml] # cp / usr/share/doc/dhcp-3.0.5/dhcpd.conf.sample / etc / dhcpd.conf <br /> The default / etc / dhcpd.conf the following meanings: <br /> ddns-update-style interim; / / set the update mode dhcp Interactive <br /> ignore client-updates; / / ignore client updates <br /> subnet 192.168.12.0 netmask 255.255.255.0 { <br /> / / Set subnet state <br /> # --- Default gateway <br /> option routers 192.168.12.1; / / set the default gateway for clients <br /> option subnet-mask 255.255.255.0; / / Set the client subnet mask <br /> option nis-domain &quot;ixdba.net&quot;; / / set the NIS domain <br /> option domain-name &quot;ixdba.net&quot;; / / set the DNS domain <br /> option domain-name-servers 192.168.12.1; / / set the DNS server address <br /> option time-offset -18000; # Eastern Standard Time / / set the time offset <br /> # Option ntp-servers 192.168.12.1; <br /> # Option netbios-name-servers 192.168.12.1; <br /> # --- Selects point-to-point node (default is hybrid). Don\'t change this unless <br /> # - You understand Netbios very well <br /> # Option netbios-node-type 2; <br /> range dynamic-bootp 192.168.12.128 192.168.12.254; / / set the address pool <br /> default-lease-time 21600; / / set the default lease, in seconds <br /> max-lease-time 43200; / / set the client up to the lease, in seconds <br /> # We want the nameserver to appear at a fixed address <br /> host ns {/ / assign a static IP address of the following settings, can not give more explanation. <br /> next-server marvin.redhat.com; <br /> hardware ethernet 12:34:56:78: AB: CD; <br /> fixed-address 207.175.42.254; <br /> } <br /> } <br /> To use the default can work, but we can also we need to be changed. <br /> Other notes: <br /> range 192.168.12.2 192.168.12.125; can assign the IP address range limit. <br /> If you want to assign a fixed IP address of IP, change it to a host, the NIC\'s Mac address and IP to bind, is the last part, converted into the corresponding on it. <br /> Segments defined in the subnet of your network card with the same IP network segment in which, such as your network card that is 192.168.0.x, and dhcp services are to the subnet 10.1.1.0 is not enough to provide services, is can not start. <br /> In this experimental environment, my dhcpd.conf as follows: <br /> [Root @ webserver html] # more / etc / dhcpd.conf <br /> ddns-update-style interim; <br /> ignore client-updates; <br /><br /> subnet 192.168.12.0 netmask 255.255.255.0 { <br /><br /> option routers 192.168.12.1; <br /> option subnet-mask 255.255.255.0; <br /><br /> option nis-domain &quot;ixdba.net&quot;;</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">option domain-name &quot;ixdb</font>a.net &quot;; <br /> option domain-name-servers 192.168.12.1; <br /> option time-offset -18000; <br /><br /> range 192.168.12.130 192.168.12.137; <br /> default-lease-time 21600; <br /> max-lease-time 43200; <br /><br /> server-name &quot;192.168.12.142&quot;; <br /> next-server 192.168.12.142; <br /> filename &quot;/ pxelinux.0&quot;; <br /><br /> host server1 { <br /> server-name &quot;192.168.12.142&quot;; <br /> next-server 192.168.12.142; <br /> hardware ethernet 00:0 C: 29:23:35: C1; <br /> fixed-address 192.168.12.131; <br /> filename &quot;/ pxelinux.0&quot;; <br /> } <br /><br /> } <br /> Among them, the need to explain there, <br /> server-name Name; <br /> The server-name statement to tell the client assigned address of the server\'s name. <br /> Name is to provide to the client\'s name. <br /> next-server Servername <br /> The next-server statement is used to specify the initial storage of the host address starting document (filename specified in the documentation). Servername is an IP address or domain name. If there is no next-server parameter sent to the client to use DHCP server address. <br /> (3) DHCP common startup mistakes <br /> A: PXELINUX start very slow loading when PXELINUX may find that when you took a long time seemed to show similar to the following line: <br /> pxelinux.cfg/01-88-99-aa-bb-cc-dd <br /> pxelinux.cfg/C000025B <br /> pxelinux.cfg/C000025 <br /> pxelinux.cfg/C00002 <br /> pxelinux.cfg/C0000 <br /> pxelinux.cfg/C000 <br /> pxelinux.cfg/C00 <br /> pxelinux.cfg/C0 <br /> pxelinux.cfg / C <br /> pxelinux.cfg / default <br /> At this point, must be confirmed in the / etc / dhcpd.conf configuration file to set a next-server tftp server address. As shown in the example, as long as the following line to: <br /> next-server 192.168.77.254; <br /> B: in.tftpd: tftp: client does not accept options (there is no acceptable option) <br /> Perhaps the course of their work in the dhcp in / var / log / messages to see some of the following warning message: <br /> in.tftpd: tftp: client does not accept options <br /> This is normal. PXELINUX can not seem to accept all of the options, but this does not affect the boot. <br /> C: socket error when running in.tftpd Tip If you see an error like: <br /> in.tftpd: cannot bind to local socket: Address already in use <br /> There may be in the / etc / xinet.d / tftp file in the server configuration error of some options. Please check carefully. <br /><br /> <font color=\"#ff0000\">Third, configure the PXE boot file</font> <br /><br /> After the tftp installed in the / directory automatically create a / tftpboot directory, this directory can be used to store the PXE boot file PXE boot files are generally path / usr/lib/syslinux/pxelinux.0, If you do not find this file, make sure the system is properly installed syslinux package, if not installed syslinux package, there is no pxelinux.0 file, here we will pxelinux.0 copied to / tftpboot directory. <br /> [Root @ webserver html] # cp / usr/lib/syslinux/pxelinux.0 / tftpboot / <br /> Next, you need to Linux system boot files on the installation CD to copy / tftpboot / directory, different versions of linux, the boot file may be different, here we use the Centos5.3 version of the CD in the CD isolinux boot file directory. The isolinux directory of all files are copied to / tftpboot directory. </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">[Root @ webserver html] # mount / dev / cdrom / mnt <br /> [Root @ webserver html] # cp / mnt / isolinux / * / tftpboot <br /> Finally, we in the / tftpboot directory to create pxelinux.cfg directory and the current / tftpboot directory isolinux.cfg files are copied to / tftpboot / pxelinux.cfg directory, and renamed the default. Operation is as follows: <br /> [Root @ webserver html] # cd / tftpboot <br /> [Root @ webserver tftpboot] # mkdir pxelinux.cfg <br /> [Root @ webserver tftpboot] # cp isolinux.cfg pxelinux.cfg / default <br /> At this point, PXE + TFTP + DHCP automatic network boot Linux system installation has been completed. <br /><br /> <font color=\"#ff0000\">Fourth, test the PXE boot function automatically</font> <br /><br /> Here we test the virtual machine through vmware, first create a vmware virtual machine, and then turn esc key to enter boot options, as shown below: <br /><br /> Start here to choose from the network, and then press Enter, if the PXE + TFTP + DHCP configured properly to connect to the system automatically starts the installation boot screen, as shown below: <br /><br /> Here so far, PXE + TFTP + DHCP network boot Linux automatically configure successful. Then you can install linux through a variety of network system. <br /><br /> Can choose to install linux system by http <br /><br /> Can choose to install via ftp linux system <br /><br /> Can choose to install linux system by NFS <br /><br /> Adjourned. . .</font> </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>','His earlier written an article to share with you the next! Overview PXE (preboot execute environment), developed by Intel\'s latest technology, working in the Client / Server network model to support the station through the network from a remote server to download images, and thus support from the...'),(45,'Linux','linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0711/315.html','http://www.ixdba.net','How to choose your own linux distribution','How_to_choose_your_own_linux_distribution','2010-07-11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> About <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/linux/\">linux</a></u> distributions, too much, probably no one can give an accurate number, but one thing is for sure, <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/linux/\">Linux</a></u> is becoming increasingly popular, in the face of so many Linux distributions, going from Go to linux system to other systems may be confusing for beginners, even the faithful Linux users do not have time and energy to try one by one, so the beginners in learning linux, you need to have a clear direction, choose a suitable system is essential to start learning linux! Here we introduce classification. </p><div style=\"text-align: center\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" height=\"148\" onclick=\"window.open(&apos;/uploads/allimg/100711/1_100711185103_1.jpg&apos;)\" src=\"http://www.ixdba.net/uploads/allimg/100711/1_100711185103_1.jpg\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" width=\"209\" /></div><p> 1.1.1 Beginners series of preferred-redhat linux in the series before learning redhat, redhat linux must first understand the following relationships between the various releases. <br /></p><p> 1. Red Hat Linux <br /> Redhat Red Hat Linux is the first release of the personal version of linux, the 1.0 version on November 3, 1994 issue. Although its history is less than other linux releases a long, but compared to a lot of Linux distributions, Red Hat\'s long history and much more. Since Red Hat 9. 0 after release, RedHat is no longer developing the company\'s Linux desktop distributions, Red Hat Linux to stop the development, and will be fully concentrate on the development of the server version, which is Red Hat Enterprise Linux version. April 30, 2004, Red Hat the company official to stop Red Hat 9. 0 version of the support, marking the official end of the Red Hat Linux. The original Red Hat Linux desktop distributions are Fedora open source community and from the plan to merge into Fedora Core release. <br /> Red Hat is currently divided into two series: the Red Hat provides technical support and updated charging Red Hat Enterprise Linux, as well as community development free from the Fedora Core. <br /></p><p> 2. Fedora Core <br /> Fedora Core (abbreviated as FC) is targeting Red Hat\'s experimental site for the new technology, many new technologies will be tested in the FC, if stable, then Red Hat will consider joining the Red Hat Enterprise Linux. <br /> Fedora Core 1 was released in late 2003, and FC is the positioning of desktop users. FC provides the latest package, while its version of the update cycle is very short, only 6 months. Since version update frequently, performance and stability can not be guaranteed, therefore, generally not recommended on the server Fedora Core. <br /> In fact, so to that, Fedora is Red Hat released Red Hat Enterprise linux version of an experiment, take the user to do the test for Red Hat Enterprise Edition released as a foundation. <br /></p><p> 3. Red Hat Enterprise Linux <br /> Red Hat Enterprise Linux (abbreviated to RHEL, Red Hat Enterprise Edition.) Red Hat is now the main job of the server version of linux development, in the version of emphasis on the performance and stability as well as hardware support. Enterprise Edition operating system, because the development cycle is longer, pay attention to performance, stability, and server software support, version updates are relatively slow. <br /> RedHat Enterprise Linux version is divided into 4 Advanced Server (AS), ES Workstation (WS), Desktop, their difference is not large, only a function of the difference. <br /></p><p> 4. Centos <br /> CentOS full name of the &quot;Community Enterprise Operating System&quot; (Community Enterprise Operating System) <br /> CentOS background: <br /> Redhat released Redhat 9. 0, no longer develop redhat 10,11 ... ..., a comprehensive shift Redhat enterprise linux (abbreviated as rhel) development, and different from the past, the new redhat Enterprise Edition requires users to first purchase lisence, redhat same time commitment to ensure the stability, security. rhel binary code is no longer available for download, but as part of redhat service, but the source code remains open. In this case, there has been centos, whitebox, dao, and so a number of open source in the enterprise version, which centos most active. <br /></p><p> Here is how to make about centos generated: </p><p><br /> CentOS community on the Redhat web site download all the source code, recompile. As AS / ES / WS is a commercial product, therefore, must identify all the Redhat\'s Logo and CentOS into their own identity. Such as the AS4. 0 SRPM original source compiled and put on Centos community logo, so that became the CentOS 4. 0. Redhat Enterprise Linux AS4 Update1 the source compiled to become a CentOS4. 1. AS4 Update2 source code compiled to become a CentOS4. 2 and so on. CentOS is produced. <br /> Therefore, it can be said of CentOS is Redhat AS / ES / WS free version can be obtained using the centos redhat enterprise linux with the same features and performance. Centos while also providing free long-term upgrade and update services. Thus, in many versions of RHEL clone, CentOS is a very outstanding very good. <br /> Although it is a RHEL clone centos, but not exactly the same, said cloning is a 100% interchangeability. In fact, different for centos, RHEL on CentOS software can not guarantee 100% above normal. <br /> To understand the difference between Redhat version series, after all. In fact, we found Why Redhat linux as a beginner to learn the reason. <br /> First of all: in the country, and even the world\'s Linux users are most familiar with, the most heard details of the distribution can be sure it is a Red Hat. Red Hat is the linux community as the &quot;boss&quot;, the U.S. company Red Hat released Red Hat linux is a commercial operation of the most successful Linux distributions, so Red Hat linux issued by a trusted company, Red Hat linux functionality and performance There is no doubt. <br /> Second: Red hat now has a huge network of user groups, network resources, the basic 90% of linux are based on Redhat linux, if you encounter any problems in the learning process, whatever the search network, there are thousands of answers to display in front of you. <br /> III: Red Hat linux version of complementary series, complement each other: If your first contact with linux, it is recommended that you install Fedora Core, Fedora Core installation is simple, good hardware support, the interface is also very beautiful, but also can experience the Redhat linux the latest features; if you have some knowledge of linux, need further study, I suggest you use the CENTOS system; if you are doing linux enterprise applications, we recommend you use RHEL version. <br /> Last: redhat wide range of applications, with typical and representative, many systems (such as red redflag, winning linux, oracle release of Enterprise Linux) are based on Red Hat linux as the base, and therefore can be said to learn the Red Hat linux, will be able to comprehend by analogy, other similar linux system can quickly mastered; around now in general are also learning to linux redhat linux based, so to facilitate communication, learning problems, more easily solved. Redhat linux while installing and using the most simple, therefore, is basically not in the &quot;loading system&quot; to waste too much time. <br /></p><p> 1.1.2 Enterprise Application preferred-suse linux <br /> The pursuit of enterprise-class applications is reliability and stability, which requires the application of building enterprise-class platform with high reliability and high stability. Enterprise linux distributions is to solve this problem. <br /> SUSE Linux is Germany\'s most famous release, around the world also enjoys a high reputation. November 4, 2003, Novell announced the company will acquire SuSE. January 2004 completion of the acquisition process, Novell SuSE also will be officially named SuSE Linux. Novell\'s acquisition of suse, speed up the development of the suse linux, suse linux server, both in the desktop market or markets are more specialized, according to incomplete statistics, suse linux linux market share in Europe is now nearly 80% share, most critical applications is built under suse linux. Suse shorter due to China, while with suse marketing model in China, the domestic short-term can not be accepted, so now suse market share in China is not great, but this does not affect the suse linux high reliability and stability the fact that, with the development of suse, suse linux in China believe that the application will be more and more. <br /></p><p> 1.1.3 Preferred-Ubuntu Linux Game <br /> Speaking of linux desktop market, Ubuntu Linux account for almost half of the desktop linux, Ubuntu Linux main linux desktop, the most beautiful interface, simple yet gorgeous, if you want entertainment under linux, Ubuntu Linux is definitely the first choice. <br /> Ubuntu is very user-friendly installation, simply follow the instructions step by step, the installation is as easy as with Windows! And, Ubuntu is best known for the most comprehensive hardware support for Linux distributions, and many other distributions can not be used or not used in the default configuration of hardware, in Ubuntu, can be easy to get. So you can install windows as easily as the installation of Ubuntu. Enjoy the fun of Ubuntu linux. </p><p><br /> 1.1.4 linux as a server is the trend </p><p><br /> In the above section introduces some of the most common linux distributions, in fact, there are many linux distributions much more common there is Debian GNU / Linux, Mandriva, Gentoo, Slackware, Knoppix, MEPIS, Xandros, domestic red flag redflag, winning linux, etc., and is not introduced one by one, in fact, look at the various linux distributions, linux release is nothing more than moving from two aspects, one is the server market, but the desktop market. <br /> As the representative of the Ubuntu Linux distribution linux desktop market is taking the route, although they bring a lot of surprises to the user, update soon, but due to windows desktop market has such a strong opponent, linux Desktop development difficult. <br /> The series version of redhat linux distributions represented by enterprise-class linux for now mainly in the server market, focusing on development of the enterprise versions of linux, suse linux as the main force also focused on developing enterprise linux above, other such domestic redhat flag, winning linux linux so key input in the server market. linux vendors are now two major release of the linux server market to go the route can be seen as an enterprise server linux has great development prospects, According to authoritative statistics, linux in the server market share continued to increase every year. <br /> In fact, many applications are for linux linux server, this book is mainly about linux on the server for a variety of applications commenced under. </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' About linux distributions, too much, probably no one can give an accurate number, but one thing is for sure, Linux is becoming increasingly popular, in the face of so many Linux distributions, going from Go to linux system to other systems may be confusing for beginners, even the faithful Linux...'),(46,'Linux','linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0421/10.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Individual works &quot;step by step Linux&quot; again','Individual_works_quotstep_by_step_Linuxquot_again','2010-04-21','0000-00-00 00:00:00','script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <font face=\"Ã¥Â¾Â®Ã¨Â½Â¯Ã©Â›Â…Ã©Â»Â‘\"><font color=\"#f00000\"><strong><font size=\"4\">Comments on the Publication <br /><br /></font></strong></font> <font size=\"3\">Press received notification of today\'s editorial, linux book &lt;&lt;a gradual <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/linux/\">Linux</a></u> &gt;&gt; has begun publishing a large number of long-awaited moment f