h=\"69%\"><div> <span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Extract the compressed file to the specified directory</span></span> </div></td></tr></tbody></table></p><div> <span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Ã‚Â </span></span> </div><div> <b><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">2. Example</span></span></b> </div><div> <span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">(1) / etc directory to compress all the files and directories, set the compression level to maximum, save to the file / opt / etc.zip.</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">[Root @ mylinux ~] # zip-9r / opt / etc.zip / etc</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">(2) the / var directory and all files in the subdirectories of compression, in addition to &quot;*. log&quot; file, the compressed file to the / opt directory.</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">[Root @ mylinux ~] # zip-r / opt / var.zip / var-x &quot;*. log&quot;</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">(3) above, / opt / etc.zip in the etc / passwd file deleted from the archive.</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">[Root @ mylinux ~] # zip / opt / etc.zip-d etc / passwd</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">deleting: etc / passwd</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">(4) modify the / etc / inittab file, hoping to change the information update to the / opt / etc.zip package.</span></span> </div><div> <span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">[Root @ mylinux ~] # zip-u / opt / etc.zip / etc / inittab</span></span> </div><div> <span st