em resources and performance of the current situation, and then targeted based on...'),(81,'Linux','linux','en','/a/os/linux/2010/0421/8.html','http://www.ixdba.net','linux tools under the flexible use of RPM','linux_tools_under_the_flexible_use_of_RPM','2010-04-21','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> 0: How to view the <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=rpm\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">rpm</span> package installation paths <br /> rpm-qpl xxxxxx.rpm <br /><br /> 1. How to install rpm <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E8%BD%AF%E4%BB%B6%E5%8C%85\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">package</span> <br /> rmp package rpm installation can use the program to complete. Execute the following <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E5%91%BD%E4%BB%A4\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">command</span> <br /> rpm-i your-package.rpm <br /> Where your-package.rpm you want to install the rpm package <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E6%96%87%E4%BB%B6\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">file</span> name, usually placed in the current <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E7%9B%AE%E5%BD%95\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">directory.</span> <br /> May occur during installation, or prompt the following warning: <br /> ... Conflict with ... might be to install the package has some files may overwrite the existing file, default is not such a case can be properly installed <br /> rpm - force-i force the installation to <br /> ... Is needed by ... <br /> ... Is not installed ... this package you do not need to install some software can be used <br /> rpm - nodeps-i to ignore the message that, rpm-i - force - nodeps to ignore all dependencies and documentation issues, what package can be installed, but this force can not be guaranteed to be completely installed package functioning <br /> 2. How to install. Src.rpm package is based on some packages. Src.rpm end, these packages are included source code rpm package needs to be <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E7%BC%96%E8%AF%91\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">compiled</span> during installation. There are two installation methods of these packages, <br /> Method One: <br /> 1. Execute rpm-i your-package.src.rpm <br /> 2. Cd / usr / src / redhat / SPECS <br /> 3. Rpmbuild-bp your-package.specs one and the same name as your package specs file <br /> 4. Cd / usr / src / redhat / BUILD / your-package / one and the same name in the directory of your package <br /> 5.. / Configure step and build common <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E6%BA%90%E7%A0%81\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">source</span> software, you can add <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E5%8F%82%E6%95%B0\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">parameters</span> <br /> 6. Make <br /> 7. Make install <br /> Method Two: <br /> 1. Execute rpm-i you-package.src.rpm <br /> 2. Cd / usr / src / redhat / SPECS <br /> The same as the first two steps and methods of a <br /> 3. Rpmbuild-bb your-package.specs one and the same name as your package specs file Then, in / usr/src/redhat/RPM/i386 / (depending on the different packages, it could be i686, noarch, etc. ) <br /> In this directory, there is a new rpm package, this is a compiled binary file. <br /> Executive rpm-i new-package.rpm to complete the installation. <br /> 3. How do I uninstall rpm packages using the command rpm-e package name, package name can include the version number and other information, but can not have the suffix. Rpm <br /> Such as the uninstall package proftpd-1.2.8-1, can use the following format: <br /> rpm-e proftpd-1.2.8-1 <br /> rpm-e proftpd-1.2.8 <br /> rpm-e proftpd- <br /> rpm-e proftpd <br /> Not one of the following formats: <br /> rpm-e proftpd-1.2.8-1.i386.rpm <br /> rpm-e proftpd-1.2.8-1.i386 <br /> rpm-e proftpd-1.2 <br /> rpm-e proftpd-1 <br /> Sometimes there will be some errors or warnings: <br /> ... Is needed by ... This shows that the software required by other software, can not easily uninstall rpm-e - nodeps to force uninstall <br /> 4. How not to install the rpm package, but access to the files and use the <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E5%B7%A5%E5%85%B7\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">tools</span> rpm2 <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=cpio\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">cpio</span> cpio <br /> rpm2cpio xxx.rpm | cpio-vi <br /> rpm2cpio xxx.rpm | cpio-idmv <br /> rpm2cpio xxx.rpm | cpio - extract - make-directories <br /> I and extract the same parameters that extract the files. v indicates that the implementation <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E8%BF%9B%E7%A8%8B\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">process</span> <br /> d and make-directory the same as that based on the original path of the file in the package build directory <br /> m file that kept updated. <br /> 5. How do I view the files with the rpm package and other information related to all of the examples below assume package mysql-3.23.54a-11 <br /> 1. My <span class=\"t_tag\" href=\"tag.php?name=%E7%B3%BB%E7%BB%9F\" onclick=\"tagshow(event)\">system</span> installed that rpm package <br /> rpm-qa about all the installed packages list if you want to find all the installed software package that contains a string sql <br /> rpm-qa | grep sql <br /> 2. How to get the full file name to a package <br /> rpm-q mysql access to mysql package installed on the system\'s full name, which you can obtain information such as the current version of the package. Information can be obtained in this example mysql-3.23.54a-11 <br /> 3. A rpm package file is installed have gone? <br /> Note that rpm-ql package name is not included here. rpm package name suffix that can only use mysql or mysql-3.23.54a-11 instead of mysql-3.23.54a-11.rpm. <br /> If you just want to know where to go into the executable program can also be used which, for example <br /> which mysql <br /> 4. A rpm package contains those files that a package is not installed, use rpm-qlp ****. rpm <br /> An already installed package, you can also use rpm-ql