. Now many people will face a problem: we take for granted the wish / lowgame / *. php files are submitted to the fastcgi analysis, the results are not so that when I visited localhost / lowgame / ddd.php time, fastcgi returns an error: <br /> No input file specified. <br /> ddd.php true existence, permissions, and no problem, apparently can not find the file fastcgi, nginx actually submitted this path / data0/htdocs/NetBeansProjects/_example/passport/lowgame/ddd.php, of course, can not find it. Try to add the following code: <br /> location ~ / lowgame /(.*/)?.* \\. (php | php5)? $ <br /> { <br /> # Fastcgi_pass unix: / tmp / php-cgi.sock; <br /> fastcgi_pass 127.0.0.1:9000; <br /> fastcgi_index index.php; <br /> include fcgi.conf; <br /> } <br /> But will be matched to the above location ~ .* \\. (Php | php5)? $, The Internet search a lot, no one used the. Then think of apache virtual host configuration has a strategy is a particular second level domain EDITORIAL, if no match to the last, and finally set up a common match. nginx is not also have this feature? The location ~ / lowgame /(.*/)?.* \\. (Php | php5)? $ Code into the location ~ .* \\. (Php | php5)? $ Code in front, finally done! </p><p> Here is my nginx configuration file: <br /> user www www; </p><p> worker_processes 2; </p><p> error_log / data0/logs/nginx_error.log crit; </p><p> pid / usr / local / webserver / nginx / nginx.pid; </p><p> # Specifies the value for maximum file descriptors that can be opened by this process. <br /> worker_rlimit_nofile 65535; </p><p> events <br /> { <br /> use epoll; <br /> worker_connections 65535; <br /> } </p><p> http <br /> { <br /> include mime.types; <br /> default_type application / octet-stream; </p><p> # Charset gb2312; </p><p> server_names_hash_bucket_size 128; <br /> client_header_buffer_size 32k; <br /> large_client_header_buffers 4 32k; <br /> client_max_body_size 8m; </p><p> sendfile on; <br /> tcp_nopush on; </p><p> keepalive_timeout 60; </p><p> tcp_nodelay