f=\"http://$host/$1$2/\">http:// $ Host / $ 1 $ 2 /</a> Permanent; <br /> } </p><p> location ~ ^ / (lowgame | lowproxy | lowadmin | passportadmin )/(.* \\. php) $ <br /> { <br /> alias / data0/htdocs/NetBeansProjects/_example / $ 1 / $ 2; <br /> fastcgi_pass 127.0.0.1:9000; <br /> fastcgi_index index.php; <br /> include fcgi.conf; <br /> } </p><p> location ~ .* \\. (php | php5)? $ { <br /> # Fastcgi_pass unix: / tmp / php-cgi.sock; <br /> fastcgi_pass 127.0.0.1:9000; <br /> fastcgi_index index.php; <br /> include fcgi.conf; <br /> } </p><p> location / lowgame / { <br /> alias / data0/htdocs/NetBeansProjects/_example/lowgame /; <br /> } </p><p> location / lowproxy / { <br /> alias / data0/htdocs/NetBeansProjects/_example/lowproxy /; <br /> } </p><p> location / lowadmin / { <br /> alias / data0/htdocs/NetBeansProjects/_example/lowadmin /; <br /> } </p><p> location / passportadmin / { <br /> alias / data0/htdocs/NetBeansProjects/_example/passportadmin /; <br /> } <br /> } </p><p> } </p><p> Note: location is written: <br /> location = / {...} # equals exact match <br /> location path {...} # path name that matches all this at the beginning, so / that matches all <br /> loation ~ regex {...} # ~ followed by a regular expression match by regular <br /> location ^ ~ regex {...} # ^ that is to take non-meaning, it should be said that the time does not match the regex, try used, not easy to use. For example: <br /> server { <br /> index index.html index.htm index.php; <br /> location ~ ^ / test / { <br /> index index.htm index.html index.php; <br /> } <br /> } <br /> Means well understood, access localhost / test / when the match location ~ ^ / test / settings, is displayed index.htm, if so what: <br /> server { <br /> index index.html index.htm index.php; <br /> location ^ ~ ^ / test / { <br /> index index.htm index.html index.php; <br /> } <br /> } <br /> At this point the meaning is clearly not &quot;subject to test / directory other than the all access are matched location ^ ~ ^ / test / settings&quot;, the author visited localhost /, still show index.html, instead of index.htm. </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' In my environment, set documentRoot directory:  root / data0/htdocs/NetBeansProjects/_example/passport;  Php file set forwarded to fastcgi:  location ~ .* \\. (php | php5)? $  {  # Fastcgi_pass unix: / tmp / php-cgi.sock;  fastcgi_pass 127.0.0.1:9000;  fastcgi_index index.php;  include fcgi.conf; ...'),(84,'Web','Web','en','/a/web/tomcat/2010/0520/107.html','http://www.ixdba.net','JVM tuning is a very simple...','JVM_tuning_is_a_very_simple','2010-05-20','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/web/tomcat/\">JVM</a></u> tuning is a very simple and very complex topic, since such problems often encountered in this summary. </p><p> Start to resolve bug started, when the Java application program memory can be allocated out of the VM, when pure, VM might be the first GC, GC finished if not enough, or the application may have a direct super enough to VM, it will throw out of memory exception. From the VM specification, we can get, about several exceptions. </p><p> <strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">java.lang.StackOverflowError: (rare) <br /> java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: heap space (more common) <br /> java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: PermGen space (often)</span></strong> </p><p> <strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: GC overhead limit exceeded (an action occurs when using a lot of memory)</span></strong> </p><p> The following are explained, from the beginning of the most common: </p><p> <strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: PermGen space</span></strong> this anomaly more common, is that JVM memory area in the Perm abnormal overflow, the JVM in the default case, Perm default is 64M, and many programs need a lot of Perm region memory, especially with to other frameworks like Spring, because of need to use dynamically generated classes, and these classes can not be GC automatically released, thus resulting in OutOfMemoryError: PermGen space exception. Solution is simple, increase the JVM\'s-XX: MaxPermSize startup parameters, we can solve this problem, such as through the use of the default variable is usually 64M [5.0 and newer: 64 bit VMs are scaled 30% larger; 1.4 amd64: 96m ; 1.3.1-client: 32m.], changed to 128M on it,-XX: MaxPermSize = 128m. If you have a 128m (Eclipse has a 128m a) to change the 256m. I usually on the server for security reasons, change the 256m. </p><p> <strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: heap space</span></strong> or other OutOfMemoryError, this exception is actually with the above exception is an exception, but the solutions are different, so separate write. Above, that exception is because the JVM\'s perm area caused less distinction between memory (JVM\'s memory is divided into young, old, perm three). And this exception is because the JVM heap memory or less total points. The solution is to change-Xms-Xmx startup parameter, usually 1-fold increase. xms is to manage the minimum amount of memory at startup, xmx tube JVM is the largest amount of memory. <br /> Note: OutOfMemoryError may have a variety of reasons, according to JVM Specification, may be about several situations, I briefly listed. stack: stack partition can not be dynamically expanded, or not enough to generate a new thread. Heap: need more memory, but can not get. Method Area: If you can not satisfy the distribution requirements. runtime constant pool (from the Method Area allocate memory) enough to create a class or interface. native method stacks can not be dynamically expanded, or create new native thread. </p><p></p><p> <strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: GC overhead limit exceeded,</span></strong> this is the type of error JDK6 Xintian. Occurs in the GC takes a lot of time when the release occurred in a small space, is a protective mechanism. JSP guide I encountered when a large Excel. The final solution is to disable the function, use the --XX:-UseGCOverheadLimit </p><p> Finally talk about <strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000\">java.lang.StackOverflowError,</span></strong> honestly I have not met the exception too, but the JVM Specification to mention, norms, said there are about several situations may throw the exception, one is the Stacks in the thread over the allowed time the other is when the native method requires more memory, and more than native method when the memory allows. According to SUN\'s documentation, improve-XX: ThreadStackSize = 512 value. </p><p> JVM memory tuning in general, group purpose is to use memory as small as possible, and make the program run properly, do not throw the net overflow bug. But should be fine minimum memory, maximum memory of the ratio of GC time to avoid wasting too much time, especially to avoid FULL GC. </p><p></p><p> Added: Since JDK1.4 added nio, nio the buffer memory is allocated and rather special (read and write streams can be shared memory). If you have a large number of data exchange, may also lead to java.lang.OutOfMemoryError. The corresponding JDK added a special parameter:-XX: MaxDirectMemorySize default is 64M, you can change something as big 128M. </p><p> -XX: MaxDirectMemorySize = &lt;size&gt; <br /> Specifies the maximum amount of memory in bytes that the Java Ã¢Â„Â¢ NIO library can allocate for direct memory buffers. The default is 64 megabytes, which corresponds to <br /> -XX: MaxDirectMemorySize = 64m. The use of direct memory buffers can minimize the copying cost when doing I / O operations. </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>','JVM tuning is a very simple and very complex topic, since such problems often encountered in this summary.  Start to resolve bug started, when the Java application program memory can be allocated out of the VM, when pure, VM might be the first GC, GC finished if not enough, or the application may...'),(85,'Web','Web','en','/a/web/tomcat/2010/0426/81.html','http://www.ixdba.net','1, Permanent Generation space...','1_Permanent_Generation_space','2010-04-26','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><div><p> <font face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><strong>1, Permanent Generation space problem</strong> <br /><br /> PermGen space stands for Permanent Generation space, refers to the memory of the permanent preservation areas OutOfMemoryError: PermGen space benefits from a surface is the memory, the solution must also be increased memory. Why talk about the benefits out of memory: This section is used to store information on Class and Meta, Class is Load in the PermGen space when they were placed in regional, and store it in different areas Instance of the Heap, GC (Garbage Collection) does not PermGen space running the main program to clean up on, so if your lot CLASS LOAD APP would then, it is possible PermGen space <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/mz/\">error</a></u> . This <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/mz/\">error</a></u> is common, JSP web server to pre compile time. <br /><br /> Correction:-Xms256m-Xmx256m-XX: MaxNewSize = 256m-XX: MaxPermSize = 256m <br /><br /> <strong>2, tomcat redeploy when outofmemory in</strong> <br /><br /> When the tomcat redeploy outofmemory in error. <br /><br /> Can have the following reasons: <br /><br /> 1, the use of the proxool, because it contains an internal proxool old version of cglib. <br /><br /> 2, log4j, not the best, only common-logging <br /><br /> 3, the old version of cglib, quick update to the latest version. <br /><br /> 4, updated to the latest hibernate3.2 <br /><br /> <strong>3, for example,</strong> <br /><br /> Here to tomcat environment for example, other WEB server such as jboss, weblogic, etc. is the same reason.</font> </p><p><br /> A, java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: PermGen space <br /> PermGen space stands for Permanent Generation space, refers to the memory of the permanent preservation areas, <br /> This memory is stored mainly by JVM Class and Meta information, Class Loader when being PermGen space will be placed in <br /> It and store the class instance (Instance) of the Heap regional differences, GC (Garbage Collection) is not in the main program running on <br /> To clean up the PermGen space, so if your application has a lot of CLASS, then, it is possible PermGen space error <br /> This error is common, JSP web server to pre compile time. If your WEB APP, who uses a lot of third-party jar, its size exceeds the size of the default jvm (4M) that will generate this error messages. <br /> Workaround: manually set the MaxPermSize size <br /><br /> Modify the TOMCAT_HOME / bin / catalina.sh <br /> In the echo &quot;Using CATALINA_BASE: $ CATALINA_BASE; above by adding the following line: <br /> <strong>JAVA_OPTS = &quot;-server-XX: PermSize = 64M-XX: MaxPermSize = 128m</strong> <br /> Recommendations: the same set of third-party jar files moved to tomcat / shared / lib directory, so you can take to reduce duplication of memory jar documentation purposes. <br /><br /> Second, java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: Java heap space <br /></p><p> Heap size settings <br /> JVM heap setting is the java program is running JVM memory space can be used to deploy the settings. JVM at startup automatically set Heap size value <br /> The initial space (ie-Xms) is the physical memory of 1 / 64, the maximum space (-Xmx) is the physical memory of 1 / 4. JVM can be used to provide the-Xmn-Xms-Xmx and other options can be set. Heap size is the size of the Young Generation and Tenured Generaion sum. <br /> Tip: In the JVM, if 98% of the time is available for the GC Heap size and less than 2% of the time to throw this exception information. <br /> Tip: Heap Size should not exceed the maximum 80% of physical memory available, the general to-Xms and-Xmx option to set to the same, while the-Xmn 1 / 4 of the-Xmx value. <br /> Workaround: manually set the Heap size <br /> Modify the TOMCAT_HOME / bin / catalina.sh <br /> In the &quot;echo&quot; Using CATALINA_BASE: $ CATALINA_BASE &quot;&quot; above, add the following line: <br /> JAVA_OPTS = &quot;-server-Xms800m-Xmx800m-XX: MaxNewSize = 256m&quot; <br /><br /> Third, the examples given below 1G memory environment java jvm parameter settings for reference: <br /><br /> JAVA_OPTS = &quot;-server-Xms800m-Xmx800m-XX: PermSize = 64M-XX: MaxNewSize = 256m-XX: MaxPermSize = 128m-Djava.awt.headless = true&quot; </p></div> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>','1, Permanent Generation space problem PermGen space stands for Permanent Generation space, refers to the memory of the permanent preservation areas OutOfMemoryError: PermGen space benefits from a surface is the memory, the solution must also be increased memory. Why talk about the benefits out of...'),(86,'Web','Web','en','/a/web/2010/0423/66.html','http://www.ixdba.net','RPM packages and source...','RPM_packages_and_source','2010-04-23','0000-00-00 00:00:00','script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Verdana; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">RPM</span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana\">packages and source packages storage location</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Verdana; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“\">/ usr / local / src <br /></span> <span style=\"font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; font-size: 9pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: Verdana\">Source package compile install location</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-family: Verdana; f