char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <font color=\"#000000\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"line-height: 150%; font-family: Verdana; font-size: 10pt\">B:</span> <font face=\"Verdana\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%; font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; font-size: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">cleaning up the system useless <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"line-height: 150%; font-family: Verdana; font-size: 10pt\">log,</span> gifted</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"line-height: 150%; font-family: Verdana; font-size: 10pt\">apache</span> <span style=\"line-height: 150%; font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; font-size: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana\">operating <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"line-height: 150%; font-family: Verdana; font-size: 10pt\">parameters.</span></span></font></font> <strong><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"line-height: 150%; font-family: Verdana; color: red; font-size: 10pt; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"> </span> <font face=\"Verdana\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%; font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; color: red; font-size: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">Open the</span> <span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"line-height: 150%; font-family: Verdana; color: red; font-size: 10pt; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: &apos;Courier New&apos;\">gc heap</span> <span style=\"line-height: 150%; font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; color: red; font-size: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\">logs to collect more usage information.</span></font></strong> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left; line-height: 150%; text-indent: 20pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; background: white; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"></p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left; line-height: 150%; text-indent: 20pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; background: white; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"></p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left; line-height: 150%; text-indent: 20pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; background: white; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <font face=\"Verdana\"><span style=\"line-height: 150%; font-family: Ã¥Â®Â‹Ã¤Â½Â“; color: red; font-size: 10pt; mso-ascii-font-family: Verdana; mso-hansi-font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;; mso-font-kerning: 0pt\"><strong>About java JVM optimization, a better understanding of the following:</strong></span></font> </p><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left; line-height: 150%; text-indent: 20pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; background: white; mso-char-indent-count: 2.0; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"></p><p> <span><font face=\"Verdana\"><font color=\"#000000\"><strong>The principle of JVM memory settings <br /></strong> <br /> The default java virtual machine the size of the relatively small, in the processing of large data will be error java: java.lang.OutOfMemoryError. <br /> Set jvm memory means, for the individual. Class, you can use the following method of Test run-time jvm memory settings. <br /> java-Xms64m-Xmx256m Test <br /> -Xms is to set the size of the memory initialization <br /> -Xmx is set to use the maximum memory size (preferably not more than the physical memory size) <br /> In weblogic, you can startweblogic.cmd in the virtual memory on the size of each domain set, the default setting is in the commEnv.cmd inside.</font></font></span> </p><div></div><p> <span><font face=\"Verdana\"><font color=\"#000000\"><strong>JVM memory tuning</strong></font></font></span> </p><div></div><p></p><div></div><div> <span><font face=\"Verdana\"><font color=\"#000000\">1. Heap Setting Java Heap and garbage collection is divided into three areas, Young, Old and Permanent. Young newly instantiated object saved. When the area is filled, GC will move to Old Area object. Permanent preservation area is responsible for reflecting the object, this article does not discuss the area. JVM\'s Heap allocation can use the-X parameter setting,</font></font></span> </div><p><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width: 90%; background: rgb(238,204,255) 0% 50%; moz-background-clip: -moz-initial; moz-background-origin: -moz-initial; moz-background-inline-policy: -moz-initial\" width=\"90%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"padding-bottom: 1.5pt; padding-left: 1.5pt; padding-right: 1.5pt; padding-top: 1.5pt\"><div align=\"left\"> <font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\"><span>-Xms</span></font> </div></td>padding-right: 1.5pt; padding-top: 1.5pt &quot;&gt; <div align=\"left\"> <font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">Initial Heap Size</font> </div></td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding-bottom: 1.5pt; padding-left: 1.5pt; padding-right: 1.5pt; padding-top: 1.5pt\"><div align=\"left\"> <font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">-Xmx</font> </div></td><td style=\"padding-bottom: 1.5pt; padding-left: 1.5pt; padding-right: 1.5pt; padding-top: 1.5pt\"><div align=\"left\"> <font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">java heap max</font> </div></td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding-bottom: 1.5pt; padding-left: 1.5pt; padding-right: 1.5pt; padding-top: 1.5pt\"><div align=\"left\"> <font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">-Xmn</font> </div></td><td style=\"padding-bottom: 1.5pt; padding-left: 1.5pt; padding-right: 1.5pt; padding-top: 1.5pt\"><div align=\"left\"> <font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">The heap size of the young generation</font> </div></td></tr></tbody></table></p><div></div><div> <font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana\">There are 2 JVM GC thread. Heap the first thread is responsible for recovery of the Young area. Lack of a second thread in the Heap, the traversal Heap, Older, upgrade the Young area. Older area size is equal to-Xmx minus the-Xmn, can not be set-Xms value is too large, because the second thread is forced to run will reduce the performance of JVM.</font> </div><div> <font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana\">Why do some programs frequent GC? The following reasons:</font> </div><div style=\"text-indent: -21pt; margin-left: 21pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\"><font color=\"#000000\"><span>l <span new=\"\" times=\"\">Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â  </span></span> Within a program called System.gc () or Runtime.gc ().</font></font> </div><div style=\"text-indent: -21pt; margin-left: 21pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\"><font color=\"#000000\"><span>l <span new=\"\" times=\"\">Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â  </span></span> Some middleware GC method calls itself, now need to set parameters against these GC.</font></font> </div><div style=\"text-indent: -21pt; margin-left: 21pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\"><font color=\"#000000\"><span>l <span new=\"\" times=\"\">Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â  </span></span> Java, Heap is too small, generally the default Heap is very small.</font></font> </div><div style=\"text-indent: -21pt; margin-left: 21pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\"><font color=\"#000000\"><span>l <span new=\"\" times=\"\">Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â Ã‚Â  </span></span> Frequent instances of objects, Release object. At this point try to save and reuse objects, such as using StringBuffer () and String ().</font></font> </div><div style=\"text-indent: -21pt; margin-left: 21pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\"><font color=\"#000000\">If you find that after each GC, Heap the remaining space will be 50% of the total space, which means your Heap is healthy.</font></font> </div><div style=\"text-indent: -21pt; margin-left: 21pt\"></div><div style=\"text-indent: -21pt; margin-left: 21pt\"> <font face=\"Verdana\"><font color=\"#000000\">Many Server-side Java programs after each GC is best to have 65% of the remaining space. Voice of experience:</font></font> </div><div> <span style=\"color: red\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><font color=\"#000000\">1. Server-side JVM is best to set-Xms and-Xmx the same value. To optimize the GC, the best so-Xmn-Xmx value is approximately equal to 1 / 3 [2].</font></font></span> </div><div> <span style=\"color: red\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><font color=\"#000000\">2. Preferably a GUI program every 10 to 20 seconds to run a GC, each time completed within half a second [2].</font></font></span> </div><div></div><div> <strong><font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana\">Note:</font></strong> </div><div></div><div> <font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana\">1. Increase the Heap size of the GC, although it will reduce the frequency, but also increased the time of each GC. And the GC is running, all user threads will be suspended, that is, during the GC, Java applications do not do any work.</font> </div><div></div><div> <font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana\">2. Heap size does not determine the memory usage of the process. Process memory usage is greater than the value of-Xmx defined as Java to allocate memory for other tasks, such as Stack and so each thread.</font> </div><div></div><div> <font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana\">3. Stack configuration</font> </div><div> <font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana\">Each thread has his own Stack.</font> </div><div><p><table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width: 90%; background: rgb(238,204,255) 0% 50%; moz-background-clip: -moz-initial; moz-background-origin: -moz-initial; moz-background-inline-policy: -moz-initial\" width=\"90%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"padding-bottom: 1.5pt; padding-left: 1.5pt; padding-right: 1.5pt; padding-top: 1.5pt\"><div align=\"left\"> <span style=\"font-size: 12pt\"><font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana\" size=\"2\">-Xss</font></span> </div></td><td style=\"padding-bottom: 1.5pt; padding-left: 1.5pt; padding-right: 1.5pt; padding-top: 1.5pt\"><div align=\"left\"> <font size=\"2\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt\"><font face=\"Verdana\"><font color=\"#000000\">Stack size per thread</font></font></span></font> </div></td></tr></tbody></table></p></div><div><font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana\">Stack size limits the number of threads. If too much like Stack cause memory leakage. Stack-Xss parameter determines the size of, for example-Xss1024K. If the Stack is too small, can lead to Stack spills.</font> </div><div></div><div> <font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana\">4. Hardware environment</font> </div><div> <font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana\">Hardware environment also affects the efficiency of GC, such as machine type, memory, swap space, and CPU number.</font> </div><div> <font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana\">If your program needs often create a lot of transient objects will lead to frequent JVM GC. This can increase your machine\'s memory, to reduce the use of Swap space [2].</font> </div><div></div><div> <font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana\">5.4 kinds of GC</font> </div><div> <font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana\">The first one is single-threaded GC, is the default GC. The GC for single CPU machines.</font> </div><div> <font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana\">The second is Throughput GC, is a multi-threaded GC, suitable for multi-CPU, a large number of threads to use the program. The second and the first GC GC similar to the difference between a GC Young area is in the collection of multi-threaded, but in the Old District and the first, still single-threaded. -XX: + UseParallelGC parameter to start the GC.</font> </div><div> <font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana\">The third type is Concurrent Low Pause GC, similar to the first, for multi-CPU, and require shorter procedures because of stagnation caused by the time GC. The GC can be recovered in the Old District the same time, run the application. -XX: + UseConcMarkSweepGC parameter to start the GC.</font> </div><div> <font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Verdana\">Fourth for the Incremental Low Pause GC, GC applications that require reduced due to the time of stagnation caused by program. The GC can be recovered in the Young area, while recovery of part of the Old District objects. -Xincgc parameter to start the GC.</font> </div><p></p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>','Today, a web server does not work, view the log. Tomcat quote the following information:Caused by: java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: allocLargeArray - Object size: 80040, Num elements: 40010The basic meaning of the above log information is the program you want to assign a size of 80040 bytes of an array...'),(149,'Technology clinic','MZ','en','/a/mz/2010/0422/37.html','http://www.ixdba.net','A few days ago met a Linux...','A_few_days_ago_met_a_Linux','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><div><div class=\"asset-body\"><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">A few days ago met a Linux Ext3 file system super block (Superblock) errors. <br /></font> </p><blockquote><pre> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">.... Bad superblock on / dev/hdc1</font> </pre></blockquote> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">A colleague to do the recovery, the results of the data are erased. Then think, then the recovery of direct fsck is wrong. The correct approach should be like this:</font> <p></p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">An error for the wrong <strong>disk (or device) block size.</strong> <br /> There are many ways you can get. For example, <br /></font> </p><blockquote><pre> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"># Tune2fs-l / dev/hdc1</font> </pre></blockquote> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">In fact, in most cases is 1 K.</font> <p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Error 2 on the current disk <strong>backup.</strong> <br /> Recover superblock (Superblock) process is actually a risky process. Do the backup to make backups. If there are other free equipment, use the dd command to back up the contents of the device.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">3 In general, the super-block wrong is the primary superblock is basically wrong in the Ext2/Ext3 file system is created, the screen will also prompt us to have in several places in the backup superblock. So how did you find these super block in place? help us see: <br /></font> </p><blockquote> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">-B superblock <br /> Instead of using the normal superblock, use an alternative <br /> superblock specified by superblock. This option is normally <br /> used when the primary superblock has been corrupted. The loca- <br /> tion of the backup superblock is dependent on the filesystem\'s <br /> blocksize. For filesystems with 1k blocksizes, <font color=\"#ff6600\">a backup <br /> superblock can be found at block 8193; for filesystems with 2k <br /> blocksizes, at block 16384; and for 4k blocksizes, at block <br /> 32768. <br /></font> <br /> Additional backup superblocks can be determined by using the <br /> mke2fs program using the-n option to print out where the <br /> superblocks were created. The-b option to mke2fs, which spec- <br /> ifies blocksize of the filesystem must be specified in order for <br /> the superblock locations that are printed out to be accurate. <br /><br /> If an alternative superblock is specified and the filesystem is <br /> not opened read-only, e2fsck will make sure that the primary <br /> superblock is updated appropriately upon completion of the <br /> filesystem check.</font> </blockquote><br /> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">4 began to recover. If the file system block size is 1K, then we can use the following command to recover: <br /></font> <blockquote><pre> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"># / Sbin/fsck.ext3-b 8193 / dev/hda4</font> </pre></blockquote><br /> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">If the alternate block (8193) also have problems, you can try 24577 (8192 * 3 +1) or 40961 (8192 * 5 +1).</font> <p></p></div><div class=\"asset-more\" id=\"more\"><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><font color=\"#ff6600\">Maybe you will see it, save the super-block location is in accordance with the laws of such 1,3,5,7. The specific location in BlockSize (8192) * N +1.</font> In more than 500M of space is such a law. less than 500M, I do not know. who know tell me, thank you.</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Also a guide:</font> <font color=\"#0082ff\" face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\"><a href=\"http://edseek.com/archives/2004/02/25/ext3-filesystem-bad-superblock-recovery/\" target=\"_blank\">Bad ext3 filesystem superblock Recovery</a></font> </p></div></div> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>','A few days ago met a Linux Ext3 file system super block (Superblock) errors.  .... Bad superblock on / dev/hdc1 A colleague to do the recovery, the results of the data are erased. Then think, then the recovery of direct fsck is wrong. The correct approach should be like this:An error for the wrong...'),(150,'Technology clinic','MZ','en','/a/mz/2010/0422/32.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Customer\'s server in the New...','Customers_server_in_the_New','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Customer\'s server in the New Year, was burned out, the customer to find out data recovery company to recover the data, but applications still can not access, it is best here to apache, apache2 fails to start, said libsasl2.so.2 find, apache can not start. <br /><br /><br /> Solution: <br /> # Whereis httpd <br /> Find your absolute path to the installation of httpd. If / usr / sbin / httpd <br /><br /> # Ldd / usr / sbin / httpd <br /> libpcre.so.0 =&gt; / lib/libpcre.so.0 (0xf6f8a000) <br /> libpcreposix.so.0 =&gt; / usr/lib/libpcreposix.so.0 (0xf6f86000) <br /> libaprutil-0.so.0 =&gt; / usr/lib/libaprutil-0.so.0 (0xf6f72000) <br /> libldap-2.2.so.7 =&gt; / usr/lib/libldap-2.2.so.7 (0xf6f41000) <br /> liblber-2.2.so.7 =&gt; / usr/lib/liblber-2.2.so.7 (0xf6f35000) <br /> libdb-4.2.so =&gt; / lib/tls/i686/libdb-4.2.so (0xf6e67000) <br /> libexpat.so.0 =&gt; / usr/lib/libexpat.so.0 (0xf6e48000) <br /> libapr-0.so.0 =&gt; / usr/lib/libapr-0.so.0 (0xf6e25000) <br /> librt.so.1 =&gt; / lib/tls/librt.so.1 (0xf6e11000) <br /> libm.so.6 =&gt; / lib/tls/libm.so.6 (0xf6dee000) <br /> libcrypt.so.1 =&gt; / lib/libcrypt.so.1 (0xf6dc0000) <br /> libpthread.so.0 =&gt; / lib/tls/libpthread.so.0 (0xf6dae000) <br /> libdl.so.2 =&gt; / lib/libdl.so.2 (0xf6daa000) <br /> libc.so.6 =&gt; / lib/tls/libc.so.6 (0xf6c82000) <br /> libresolv.so.2 =&gt; / lib/libresolv.so.2 (0xf6c6e000) <br /> libsasl2.so.2 =&gt; not found <br /> libssl.so.4 =&gt; / lib/libssl.so.4 (0xf6c26000) <br /> libcrypto.so.4 =&gt; / lib/libcrypto.so.4 (0xf6b3e000) <br /> / Lib/ld-linux.so.2 (0xf6fab000) <br /> libgssapi_krb5.so.2 =&gt; / usr/lib/libgssapi_krb5.so.2 (0xf6b29000) <br /> libkrb5.so.3 =&gt; / usr/lib/libkrb5.so.3 (0xf6ac4000) <br /> libcom_err.so.2 =&gt; / lib/libcom_err.so.2 (0xf6ac1000) <br /> libk5crypto.so.3 =&gt; / usr/lib/libk5crypto.so.3 (0xf6aa0000) <br /> libz.so.1 =&gt; / usr/lib/libz.so.1 (0xf6a90000) <br /><br /><br /> # Whereis libsasl2.so.2 <br /> / Usr/local/lib/libsasl2.so.2 <br /><br /> / Usr/local/lib/libsasl2.so.2.0.21 <br /><br /> ls-l / usr/local/lib/libsasl2.so.2 <br /> Find / usr/local/lib/libsasl2.so.2 ==&gt; / usr/local/lib/libsasl2.so.2.0.21 <br /><br /> So ln-s / usr/local/lib/libsasl2.so.2.0.21 / lib/libsasl2.so.2 <br /><br /> Then check again: # ldd / usr / sbin / httpd <br /><br /> libpcre.so.0 =&gt; / lib/libpcre.so.0 (0xf6f8a000) <br /> libpcreposix.so.0 =&gt; / usr/lib/libpcreposix.so.0 (0xf6f86000) <br /> libaprutil-0.so.0 =&gt; / usr/lib/libaprutil-0.so.0 (0xf6f72000) <br /> libldap-2.2.so.7 =&gt; / usr/lib/libldap-2.2.so.7 (0xf6f41000) <br /> liblber-2.2.so.7 =&gt; / usr/lib/liblber-2.2.so.7 (0xf6f35000) <br /> libdb-4.2.so =&gt; / lib/tls/i686/libdb-4.2.so (0xf6e67000) <br /> libexpat.so.0 =&gt; / usr/lib/libexpat.so.0 (0xf6e48000) <br /> libapr-0.so.0 =&gt; / usr/lib/libapr-0.so.0 (0xf6e25000) <br /> librt.so.1 =&gt; / lib/tls/librt.so.1 (0xf6e11000) <br /> libm.so.6 =&gt; / lib/tls/libm.so.6 (0xf6dee000) <br /> libcrypt.so.1 =&gt; / lib/libcrypt.so.1 (0xf6dc0000) <br /> libpthread.so.0 =&gt; / lib/tls/libpthread.so.0 (0xf6dae000) <br /> libdl.so.2 =&gt; / lib/libdl.so.2 (0xf6daa000) <br /> libc.so.6 =&gt; / lib/tls/libc.so.6 (0xf6c82000) <br /> libresolv.so.2 =&gt; / lib/libresolv.so.2 (0xf6c6e000) <br /> libsasl2.so.2 =&gt; / lib/libsasl2.so.2 (0xf6c5a000) <br /> libssl.so.4 =&gt; / lib/libssl.so.4 (0xf6c26000) <br /> libcrypto.so.4 =&gt; / lib/libcrypto.so.4 (0xf6b3e000) <br /> / Lib/ld-linux.so.2 (0xf6fab000) <br /> libgssapi_krb5.so.2 =&gt; / usr/lib/libgssapi_krb5.so.2 (0xf6b29000)</font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">libkrb5.so.3 =&gt; / usr/lib/libkrb5.so.3 (0xf6ac4000) <br /> libcom_err.so.2 =&gt; / lib/libcom_err.so.2 (0xf6ac1000) <br /> libk5crypto.so.3 =&gt; / usr/lib/libk5crypto.so.3 (0xf6aa0000) <br /> libz.so.1 =&gt; / usr/lib/libz.so.1 (0xf6a90000) <br /><br /><br /><br /> Restart httpd, OK the.</font> </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>','Customer\'s server in the New Year, was burned out, the customer to find out data recovery company to recover the data, but applications still can not access, it is best here to apache, apache2 fails to start, said libsasl2.so.2 find, apache can not start.  Solution:  # Whereis httpd  Find your...'),(151,'Technology clinic','MZ','en','/a/mz/2010/0421/15.html','http://www.ixdba.net','vsftpd 500 OOPS: cannot change...','vsftpd_500_OOPS_cannot_change','2010-04-21','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><div> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">vsftpd 500 OOPS: cannot change directory <br /><br /> Today in the ftp configuration, all configuration is completed, start the vsftpd, user login through ftp, actually an error: <br /> C: \\&gt; ftp 10.10.1.239</font> </div><div> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Connected to 10.10.1.239 <br /> 220 (vsFTPd 2.0.5) <br /> User (10.10.1.239: (none)): xaftp <br /> 331 Please specify the password. <br /> Password: <br /></font> <font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Tahoma\"><strong>500 OOPS: cannot change directory: / home / xaftp <br /></strong> Login failed. <br /> ftp&gt; ls <br /> 500 OOPS: child died <br /> Connection closed by remote host. <br /><br /> Find this very strange problem, configuration, certainly no problem, always prompt <strong>500 OOPS: cannot change directory: / home / xaftp</strong> <br /><br /> Solution: <br /> In the terminal enter the command: <br /> setsebool ftpd_disable_trans 1 <br /> service vsftpd restart <br /> To OK! <br /><br /> In fact, this is set SELinux commands. <br /> In fact, the man knows what setsebool: <br /> NAME <br /> setsebool - set SELinux boolean value <br /><br /> In unfamiliar SELnux before they can turn off the SELinux. Have time to study under SELinux. <br /> But do not want to use SELinux in familiar circumstances can the SELinux set to Permissive, SELinux rules that start, but only to irregularities in the record to the log.</font></font> </div><p></p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>','vsftpd 500 OOPS: cannot change directory  Today in the ftp configuration, all configuration is completed, start the vsftpd, user login through ftp, actually an error:  C: \\> ftp 10.10.1.239Connected to 10.10.1.239  220 (vsFTPd 2.0.5)  User (10.10.1.239: (none)): xaftp  331 Please specify the...'),(152,'Technology clinic','MZ','en','/a/mz/2010/0421/14.html','http://www.ixdba.net','su: / bin / bash: Permission deni','su__bin__bash_Permission_deni','2010-04-21','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><div> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Customers a <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/db/oracle/\">oracle</a></u> suddenly goes down, the business started, customers subconsciously to reboot the server, the system is up and ready to switch to the <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/db/oracle/\">oracle</a></u> user to start the database, how can not su to switch, really stoked Yeah, described as follows: <br /> Under the root user, su to a normal user oracle, get the following error: <br /><br /> [Root @ localhost ~] # su - oracle <br /> su: warning: cannot change directory to / home / oracle: Permission denied <br /> su: / bin / bash: Permission denied <br /><br /> The oracle user can not log in directly, made the same mistake. <br /><br /> This is a very strange question, in the end is what causes it? Ideas are as follows: <br /> 1, program execution permission problems <br /> 2, the program depends on shared library permissions problem <br /> 3, directory permission issues <br /> 4, the root space. <br /><br /> Check the / bin / bash, permissions correctly, check the / home / oracle permissions correctly, check / lib/ld- ***. so, permissions are correct. <br /><br /> Continue to debug, check the / etc / passwd, the oracle\'s home set to / tmp, the / tmp set to 777, this authority should be the most relaxed. <br /><br /> The same error su. <br /><br /> That is, 777 users can not access oracle permission / tmp. <br /><br /> Problem in the end there where? <br /><br /> Finally, star command, see the problem simply, <br /> [Root @ localhost ~] # stat / <br /> Output is as follows: Because you can not see ls. <br /> File: &quot;/&quot; <br /> Size: 1024 Blocks: 2 IO Block: 1024 directory <br /> Device: 803h/2051d Inode: 2 Links: 22 <br /> Access: (0666/drw-rw-rw-) Uid: (0 / root) Gid: (0 / root) <br /> Access: 2007-12-01 22:28:48.000000000 +0800 <br /> Modify: 2007-12-01 22:28:34.000000000 +0800 <br /> Change: 2007-12-01 23:17:35.000000000 +0800 <br /><br /> Problems arose, where permission is wrong, X caused the loss of privileges. <br /><br /> [Root @ localhost ~] # chmod 755 / <br /><br /><br /> Modifications, the problem disappeared. <br /><br /> Produce the problem: <br /> The first, chmod 666 /, can lead to. <br /><br /> Or, <br /> The second, chmod 700 / lib / ld-xxxx.so, can also lead to su to fail. <br /><br /> Are interested can try their own. <br /><br /> / Loss of privileges for various user runs on their own daemon also the same effect.</font> </div> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>','Customers a oracle suddenly goes down, the business started, customers subconsciously to reboot the server, the system is up and ready to switch to the oracle user to start the database, how can not su to switch, really stoked Yeah, described as follows:  Under the root user, su to a normal user...'),(153,'Technology clinic','MZ','en','/a/mz/2010/0421/11.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Argument list too long &quot;error solution','Argument_list_too_long_quoterror_solution','2010-04-21','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><div><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">This article is a response a few days ago a friend of the forum questions, free today, order a bit, post it, for your reference! <br /></font> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">When Linux, try to pass too many arguments to a <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/\">system</a></u> command (ls *; cp *; rm *; cat *; etc ...), they will appear &quot;Argument list too long&quot; <a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/mz/\"><u>error</u></a> . This article will provide 4 solution, the degree of complexity from low to high order.</font> </p><p> <strong><font color=\"#ff0000\" face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Method # 1: command line parameters manually into smaller pieces</font></strong> </p><p> <font face=\"Tahoma\" size=\"2\">Example 1</font> </p><p><br /> mv [al] * ../directory2 </p><p> mv [mz] * ../directory2 </p><p> This is the 4 methods in the most simple, but far from ideal. You must have the means to the average split files, but for very many cases the number of documents, you need to enter the command N times. </p><p> <font color=\"#ff0000\"><strong>Method # 2: Use the find command</strong></font> </p><p> Example 2 <br /><br /><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.ixdba.net/hbcms/upload/image/big/54/544e77b81bf490ee5d212961a59c067c.jpg\" /></p><p> Method 2 commands through the find filter the list of files, to meet the requirements of the documents passed to the series of commands. </p><p> Find command has the advantage of a very powerful filtering capabilities, and, perhaps most important, this method requires only one line of command. </p><p> The only drawback is that Method 2 need to traverse the file, so time-consuming. </p><p><br /> <font color=\"#ff0000\"><strong>Method # 3: Create a function</strong></font> </p><p> Example 3 </p><p> #! / Bin / bash </p><p> # Set the folder to delete <br /> RM_DIR = \'/ data / files\' </p><p> cd $ RM_DIR <br /> for I in `ls` <br /> do <br /> rm-f $ I <br /> done </p><p><br /> <font color=\"#ff0000\"><strong>Method # 4: Re-compile the Linux kernel</strong></font> </p><p> The last method requires two words: caution, this method is very high, so there is no linux user experience is best not to try. In addition, permanent use, be sure to thoroughly test the system environment. </p><p> Method 4 only need to manually add the kernel command line parameters assigned to the number of pages. Open include / linux / binfmts.h file, near the beginning of the file location in the following lines: </p><p> / * </p><p> * MAX_ARG_PAGES defines the number of pages allocated for arguments </p><p> * And envelope for the new program. 32 should suffice, this gives </p><p> * A maximum env + arg of 128kB w/4KB pages! </p><p> * / </p><p> # Define MAX_ARG_PAGES 32 </p><p> In order to increase the allocation of the memory cell command line parameters, just assign a larger value MAX_ARG_PAGES, save, recompile, install, restart, get </p><p> In my system, I MAX_ARG_PAGES value to 64 to solve all the problems. After changing this value, I have not encountered any problems. This is understandable, when MAX_ARG_PAGES was changed to 64, the longest line of argument only with 256KB of system memory - the hardware standards for nothing now. </p><p> Obviously the advantages of Method 4, and now you just run the command as usual. Shortcomings are obvious, if the memory allocated to the command line is greater than the available system memory, the system itself may lead to denial of service attack (DoS attack), causing system crashes. Especially for multi-user system, even a small increase in memory allocation will have a significant impact, because each user is assigned to the extra memory. Therefore, we must fully tested to determine whether your system can use 4. </p></div> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>','This article is a response a few days ago a friend of the forum questions, free today, order a bit, post it, for your reference! When Linux, try to pass too many arguments to a system command (ls *; cp *; rm *; cat *; etc ...), they will appear \"Argument list too long\" error . This article will...'),(154,'Technology clinic','MZ','en','/a/mz/2010/0421/12.html','http://www.ixdba.net','No space left on device: mod_rewrite: could not create rewri','No_space_left_on_device_mod_rewrite_could_not_create_rewri','2010-04-21','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' (Editor: South African Ant)...'),(155,'Storage','Storage','en','/a/st/2010/0711/307.html','http://www.ixdba.net',' On the articles we analyzed...','_On_the_articles_we_analyzed','2010-07-11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> On the articles we analyzed the inner workings of raid5 and raid10 details, here we mainly analyze the <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/st/\">storage</a></u> array, the bottleneck, because the emergence of bottlenecks, and the raid is a very different way, so we need to analyze the specific differences in raid5 and raid10. <br /> The bottleneck is mainly reflected in the array 2, the throughput and IOPS. </p><p> 1, the throughput of the throughput depends on the array architecture, the size of the Fibre Channel (now the array are generally fiber array, as such SSA SCSI array, we do not discuss), and the number of hard drives. Array architecture varies with each array, they also exist within the bandwidth (similar to the pc the system bus), but under normal circumstances, the internal bandwidth is designed to be adequate, not where the bottleneck. <br /> The impact of fiber channel is relatively large, such as data warehousing environment, data flow requirements of a large, and a 2Gb Fibre card, can support the maximum flow should be 2Gb / 8 (small B) = 250MB / s ( Big B) the actual flow, when the four fiber cards in order to achieve 1GB / s of the actual flow, so the data warehouse environment can be considered for the fiber card 4Gb. <br /> Finally, talk about hard limits, here is the most important bottlenecks in the current surface, when no longer exists, depends on the number of hard drives, and I look at the different hard drives listed below can support the flow of size: <br /> 10 K rpm 15 K rpm ATA <br /> --- --- --- <br /> 10M / s 13M / s 8M / s <br /> So, assuming there is an array of optical fiber 120 15K rpm hard disk, the drive can support the largest flow is 120 * 13 = 1560MB / s, 2Gb Fibre card if it is, you may need six to be able to, and 4Gb Fibre Cards 3-4 is enough. </p><p> 2, IOPS <br /> The main decision depends on the array IOPS algorithm, cache hit rate, and the number of disks. Array algorithm for different arrays vary, as we have recently encountered in the hds usp above, probably because ldev (lun) queue or resource constraints exist, and a single ldev the iops would not increase, so, before using this store is necessary to understand some of the storage algorithm rules and restrictions. <br /> cache hit rate depends on the data distribution, cache size the size of the data access rules, and cache algorithms, if the full discussion down here will become very complicated, can have a good discussion of the day. I am here only to emphasize a cache hit rate, if an array, read cache hit rate as high as possible, the general said it could support more IOPS, Why? The following should be discussed with us the hard disk IOPS with relationship. <br /> Hard constraints, each physical hard disk can handle is limited IOPS, such as 10 K rpm 15 K rpm ATA <br /> --- --- --- <br /> 10,015,050 <br /> Similarly, if there is an array of optical fiber 120 15K rpm hard drive, then it can sustain the maximum IOPS of 120 * 150 = 18,000, the limit of the theoretical value for the hardware, if more than this value, the hard disk of the response may become very slow and can not properly provide services. <br /> In addition, we also discussed on the article in raid5 and raid10, read iops no difference, however, the same business writing iops, ultimately rests on the disk iops there is a difference, and we evaluated it is exactly the disk IOPS, limit if it reaches the disk, the performance is certainly not increase the. <br /> We assume that a case, the business of iops is 10,000, read cache hit rate is 30%, 60% iops read, write iops 40%, the disk number is 120, then calculate the raid5 and raid10\'s case, each a disk iops have. </p><p> IXDBA.NET Technical Community </p><p> raid5: </p><p> Single-block disk iops = (10000 * (1-0.3) * 0.6 + 4 * (10000 * 0.4)) / 120 <br /> = (4200 + 16000) / 120 <br /> = 168 <br /> Here 10000 * (1-0.3) * 0.6 that is read iops, ratio is 0.6, get rid of cache hit, actually, only 4,200 iops <br /> The 4 * (10000 * 0.4) that the written iops, because each write, in raid5, the actual occurrence of the four io, so write iops to 16,000 </p><p> Raid5 in order to consider when writing, it read 2 hits can also occur, so a more accurate calculation is: </p><p> Single-block disk iops = (10000 * (1-0.3) * 0.6 + 2 * (10000 * 0.4) * (1-0.3) + 2 * (10000 * 0.4)) / 120 <br /> = (4200 + 5600 + 8000) / 120 <br /> = 148 <br /> Iops calculated as a single disk 148, the basic disk limit reached </p><p> raid10 </p><p> Single-block disk iops = (10000 * (1-0.3) * 0.6 + 2 * (10000 * 0.4)) / 120 <br /> = (4200 + 8000) / 120 <br /> = 102 <br /> You can see, because raid10 for a write operation, occurs only 2 times io, therefore, the same pressure, the same disk, each disk iops only 102, far below the limit of the disk iops. </p><p> In a practical case, a lot of pressure recovery standby (here mainly to write, and write a small io), using a raid5 solution, found poor performance, by analyzing each disk iops during peak periods , fast 200, resulting in extremely slow response speed giant. Later transformed into raid10, to avoid this performance problem, each disk iops down to 100 or so. <br /></p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' On the articles we analyzed the inner workings of raid5 and raid10 details, here we mainly analyze the storage array, the bottleneck, because the emergence of bottlenecks, and the raid is a very different way, so we need to analyze the specific differences in raid5 and raid10.  The bottleneck is...'),(156,'Storage','Storage','en','/a/st/2010/0711/306.html','http://www.ixdba.net',' How to choose the right RAID...','_How_to_choose_the_right_RAID','2010-07-11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> How to choose the right RAID level? </p><p> There are different RAID configuration or &quot;class&quot;, each level has its own unique advantages. Understanding will enable you to determine the RAID level server reliability, data availability and storage performance of the right combination to meet specific e-business needs. Intel Integrated RAID software supports the most widely used RAID level: 0,1,5, and 10. </p><p> RAID 0 level will be assigned to the data base with more than one disk, there is no redundancy or parity. The main features of the RAID level is extremely high data throughput speeds. Data access to multiple disks make disk access more efficient, which improves read performance data. Any one disk fails the data stored will be lost </p><p> Copy using two hard drives store data, we implemented a RAID1-level (called disk mirroring), in most cases through the software. If a hard disk fails, it will be all the data (and software applications) to save to another hard disk. Although it provides maximum fault tolerance, but requires twice the disk number, so RAID1 level is extremely expensive option. With the declining cost of disk technology, RAID1-level optimization of data availability has become a viable option. </p><p> RAID 5 level will baseband section and the &quot;parity&quot; the combination together, this case, the data distribution in the online group\'s hard drive. Parity RAID controller data to understand the data stored on your hard drive. Suppose that a hard disk fails, the controller can use the parity information to re-create the lost data. RAID5-level data to allow both read and write, which is data-intensive applications that require high performance provided support. You can adjust the size of the baseband section to optimize performance, the Intel Integrated RAID software support this feature. RAID5 reasonable price level provides the best performance and data security, so far it is very popular. </p><p> RAID 10 level (0 +1) is a RAID0 and RAID1-level combination of grade, it will mirror the baseband section, and together the disk. 0 RAID10 level provides a fast performance and data protection features. In this configuration, the data is distributed across several hard disk (which is similar with the 0 level), and the data of each disk are copied to another disk, thereby protecting the data. We recommend that the best performance and data availability requirements of a small network with 10. </p><p> From large databases to e-mail systems and Web servers, they all select the appropriate RAID configuration are required to provide all the e-commerce data protection, server reliability and storage performance.. </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' How to choose the right RAID level?  There are different RAID configuration or \"class\", each level has its own unique advantages. Understanding will enable you to determine the RAID level server reliability, data availability and storage performance of the right combination to meet specific...'),(157,'Storage','Storage','en','/a/st/2010/0711/305.html','http://www.ixdba.net','To implement iSCSI read and...','To_implement_iSCSI_read_and','2010-07-11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <span style=\"font-size: x-small\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\">To implement iSCSI read and write, in addition to the use of specific hardware devices, but also by software methods, the server-side simulation for the iSCSI initiator or target side, the use of existing processor card with ordinary Ethernet iSCSI connectivity resources to achieve .</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-size: x-small\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\">iSCSI or internet SCSI, is the IETF developed a storage transport protocol standard for the SCSI data block image into Ethernet data packets. iSCSI protocol is essentially a SCSI across the IP network to transmit data block approach, read and write requests initiated by the source of equipment called the Initiator (initiator), the requested destination device is known as Target. In this way the network in IP mode on a block-level access to large amounts of data.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-size: x-small\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\">To implement iSCSI read and write, in addition to using specific hardware device, but also through software means, the server-side simulation for the iSCSI initiator or target side, the use of existing Ethernet network processors and general resources to achieve the iSCSI connection card . At present, most of the iSCSI Target simulation software to be paid for mostly commercial software, but there are many free iSCSI initiator software is available for selection.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-size: x-small\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\">IXDBA.NET Technical Community</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-size: x-small\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\">Microsoft iSCSI Initiator</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-size: x-small\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\">Microsoft provides software initiated iSCSI that allows Windows client initiated iSCSI Ethernet card into the device simulation in order to iSCSI target devices on the network access demand launched to build iSCSI online.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-size: x-small\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\">The latest version of Microsoft iSCSI Initiator version 2.04, supports Windows 2000/XP/Server 2003 and other Microsoft operating environment, and the respective support x64, IA64, x86 processor platforms such as the version. Download the installation is complete, the Discovery menu, enter the iSCSI target device or iqn IP address, you can choose the Target menu to establish a connection with the iSCSI device, through the IP network to access iSCSI storage devices, also supports multi-path transmission.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-size: x-small\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\">Linux-iSCSI</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-size: x-small\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\">There are two versions of Linux kernel 2.4/2.6\'s iSCSI Initiator, in use, the system must be ready kernel-source, kernel, gcc, perl, Apache, and other related files. Download and complete the compilation, the first / etc / iscsi.conf iSCSI configuration within the configuration to match the current iSCSI target device using the correct URL, user name and password, next to # / etc / init.d / iscsi start start iSCSI devices, and disk partition fdisk command, and finally with the mkdir and mount command to mount the disk drive.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-size: x-small\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\">Solaris iSCSI Initiator</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-size: x-small\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\">Solaris 10 has built-in iSCSI Initiator software, including SPARC 64, x64 and IA-32 and other processor platforms can support. Sun related to the iSCSI driver integrated iSCSI Device Driver and Utilities updates, the current version has been updated to 5.10.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-size: x-small\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\">Use, first with the svcadm enable svc: / network / iscsi_initiator first startup instruction format iSCSI Initiator, the operation mainly depends on the next iscsiadm command, first to iscsiadm add discovery-address command to set the target device address, and then iscsiadm modify initiator-node changes the connection between the target device settings, and then order using the devfsadm-c iscsi, format, newfs command to create a new disk and other areas, the last area and then mount command to mount it to a disk. <br /></span></span> </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>','To implement iSCSI read and write, in addition to the use of specific hardware devices, but also by software methods, the server-side simulation for the iSCSI initiator or target side, the use of existing processor card with ordinary Ethernet iSCSI connectivity resources to achieve .iSCSI or...'),(158,'Storage','Storage','en','/a/st/2010/0711/304.html','http://www.ixdba.net',' Common data backup systems...','_Common_data_backup_systems','2010-07-11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> Common data backup <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/\">systems</a></u> are Host-Base, LAN-Base Structure-based SAN LAN-Free, Server-Free and other structures. </p><p> Host-Based backup: </p><p> Host-Based is the traditional structure of the data backup tape library in this structure directly connected to the server, and only data backup service for servers. In most cases, the backup server comes with most of the tape drive, the backup operation is by manual operation is often conducted in a way. </p><p> Host-Based backup structure has the advantage of fast data transfer, backup and simple management; disadvantage is not conducive to the sharing of backup system is not suitable for large data backup requirements now. </p><p> LAN-Based backup: </p><p> LAN-Based backup data in the system is web-based transmission. Which to configure a server as backup server, which will be responsible for the entire system backup operations. Tape library is connected to a server, data backup backup object in the data over the network to implement a backup tape library. </p><p> LAN-Based backup structure has the advantage of saving investment, tape library sharing, centralized backup management; its disadvantage is that the network transmission pressure. </p><p> LAN-Free backup: </p><p> LAN-Free and Server-Free backup system is based on SAN ( <a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/st/\"><u>storage</u></a> area network) based on its structure as shown below. SAN-based backup is a completely solve the need to occupy the traditional backup solutions for LAN bandwidth issues. It uses a new architecture, the tape libraries and disk arrays each act as independent fiber optic nodes, multiple hosts to share a tape library backup, data flow through the network and not directly from the disk array Chuandao tape library, network bandwidth is a need (LAN-Free) solutions. </p><p> With the current SAN technology continues to progress, LAN-Free structure is already quite mature, and Server-Free backup structure is not mature enough. </p><p> LAN-Free has the advantage of unified management of data backup, backup speed, network transmission pressure is small, tape library resource sharing; disadvantage is that high investment. </p><p> Using IBM Tivoly Storage Manager software, with IBM LTO tape library, etc., can achieve all of these backups. </p><p></p><p> other <br /> The choice of data backup </p><p> The main ways of the current data backup: LAN backup, LAN Free backup and SAN Server-Free backup of three. LAN backup for all storage types are available, LAN Free backup and SAN Server-Free backup for SAN-based storage only. </p><p> Traditional LAN-based backup requires the backup on each host to install a tape backup on the local system, using LAN backup strategy, when the data is not very big, centralized backup can be used. A central backup server will be installed in the LAN, and then the application server and workstation configured as a backup server to the client. Accept the central backup server running the backup on the client agent\'s request, the data passed to it through the management LAN, connected to a local tape drive resources. This approach provides a centralized, easy to manage backup program, and through the sharing of tape drives in the network resource efficiency. </p><p> LAN-Free backup of the data transmitted through the LAN, when a larger amount of data to backup, backup tight time window, the network prone to clogging. In the SAN environment, can be stored in the network LAN-Free backup, you need to backup the server through the SAN to connect to the tape machine, the LAN-Free backup client software trigger, the read data to back up, back up through the SAN to a shared the tape drive. This independent network LAN traffic can not be transferred, and its CPU resources required to operate way below the LAN, because the fiber channel connection does not require the server\'s TCP / IP stack, and some level of error checking can be within the Fibre Channel hardware to complete. In many solutions require a host to manage the shared storage devices and data used to find and restore the backup database. </p><p> SAN Server-Free Backup LAN Free backup of the need to take back the host CPU resources, if the backup process can be completed within the SAN, and a large number of data streams without flow through the server, you can greatly reduce the backup of the production system. SAN Server-Free backup is one such technology. </p><p> Backup the current mainstream software, such as IBM Tivoli, Veritas, were in support of the three backup programs. Three programs, LAN backup of the smallest amount of data, most of the server resource consumption, the lowest cost; LAN free backup data volume number, smaller footprint on the server, the cost higher; SAN Server-free backup solution to backup in a short time large amounts of data, at least on the server resource consumption, but the highest cost. Small customers can choose according to the actual situation. <br /> other </p><p> Traditional Backup: How helpless wits </p><p> In the traditional backup mode, each host is equipped with a dedicated disk or tape storage systems, host of the data must be backed up to tape in the device or special local disk array. Thus, even if a tape drive (or tape library) is idle, the other host can not use it for backup, the tape resource utilization is low. In addition, different operating system platforms used in backup and recovery procedures are generally not the same, which makes the backup job and overall management of resources becomes more complex. </p><p> Later, to produce a special tape to overcome the low utilization rate of the improvements of the system: the resource by a master tape backup / restore server control, and backup and recovery process is controlled by some management software. Master backup server to receive the other server through LAN or WAN incoming data and the disk or tape into the public system. This centralized storage in ways that greatly improved the efficiency of resource use tape. But it also has a fatal deficiency: network bandwidth will be the backup and recovery process of the potential bottlenecks. </p><p> Is there a more advanced solution, when the backup system to minimize resource consumption, while ensuring the system\'s high availability and flexibility? </p><p> LAN-free backup: The first one mundane children </p><p> One way is to use LAN-free technology. The so-called LAN-free, the data is backed up directly without a local area network, that user can simply tape drive or tape library and other backup device connected to the SAN, each server to be backed up data can be sent directly to the shared backup device do not have to go through local area network links. Because the server to share large data storage devices is carried out through the SAN network, LAN, bear only the communication between the server (rather than data transfer) missions. </p><p> 2 common means of implementation </p><p> LAN-free implementation of a variety of ways. Typically, users need for each server with a Fibre Channel adapter, the adapter is responsible for these servers connected to one or more tape drives (or tape library) connected to SAN. At the same time, with a particular need for the server management software, through which the system able to block format data from the server memory, the SAN tape drive or transferred to the tape library. </p><p> There is also a common implementation of LAN-free approach, in this structure, the main backup server management software can start the other server data backup operations. Block format of the data from the disk array through the SAN to store data transmitted to the temporary memory of the backup server, after transmission through SAN to the tape drive or tape library. </p><p> LAN-free backup inadequate </p><p> &quot;No one is perfect&quot;, LAN-free technology is also less than obvious. First, it is still involved in the server backup data from one storage device to another storage device in the process, to a certain extent, take up valuable CPU processing time and server memory. Another problem is, LAN-free recovery technology, unsatisfactory, it is very dependent on the user\'s application. Many products do not support file-level or directory-level recovery, image-level recovery to become more common. Image-level recovery is to copy the image from the tape back to disk, if you need to quickly restore a single file, the whole operation will become very troublesome. </p><p> In addition, different vendors implement LAN-free mechanism to vary, which causes the backup process will be required for compatibility problems between systems. </p><p> LAN-free implementation of the complex and often require large hardware and software purchasing costs. </p><p> Serverless Backup: icing on the cake The second measure children </p><p> Another way to reduce resource consumption of the system approach is to use no server (Serverless) backup technology. It is an extension of LAN-free, can provide data to the SAN structure in the direct transmission between the two storage devices, usually between disk arrays and tape libraries. One of the main advantages of this approach is the need for caching data in the server, significantly reduces host CPU occupancy, improve the efficiency of the operating system to help companies do more work. </p><p> 2 common means of implementation </p><p> As with LAN-free, non-implementation of the server backups are also several ways. Typically, the backup data through a device called the Data Mover transfers from the disk array to the tape library. The device may be Fibre Channel switches, storage routers, intelligent tape or disk device or a server. Data Mover command is executed to transfer data from one storage device to another device. One way to implement this process is by means of SCSI-3 extended copy command, which enables the server to send commands to the storage device, instructions which transfer data directly to another device, without going through server memory. Received extended copy data mover command, perform the appropriate function. </p><p> Another method is to use the Network Data Management Protocol (NDMP). This agreement is actually for the server, backup and recovery applications and backup devices and other components to act as an interface between the communication. In the implementation process, NDMP to commands from the server to the backup application, with the NDMP-compliant backup software will start the actual work of data transmission and data transmission is not through the server memory. The purpose is to facilitate the NDMP heterogeneous backup and recovery environment process and enhance backup and recovery of different vendors management software and storage hardware compatibility. </p><p> Advantages of server-free backup </p><p> No server backup and LAN-free backup has many similar advantages. If no server backup, the source device, the destination device and the SAN devices are the main components of the data channel. Although the server is still involved in the backup process, but greatly reduce the burden, because it is basically similar to the role of traffic police, only for the command, not used for loading and transport, not the primary backup data channel. </p><p> Serverless backup technology to shorten backup and recovery with the time spent advantages. Because the backup process on the dedicated high-speed storage network, and the decision is a storage device throughput speed, rather than the server\'s processing power, so the system performance will be greatly enhanced. In addition, if no-server backup technology, data can be transmitted in the form of data streams to multiple tape libraries or disk arrays. </p><p> The drawback, though greatly reduced the burden on the server, but still need a backup application software (and its host server) to control the backup process. Metadata must be recorded in the database backup software, which still need to take up CPU resources. </p><p> As with LAN-free, non-server backup mentioned above may lead to the same kind of compatibility issues. Moreover, no server backup may be difficult and costly. Finally, if no server backup applications to be more extensive and greater recovery function remains to be improved. </p><p> Balancing the pros and cons and then decided upon </p><p> We discussed earlier under the Fibre Channel environment, LAN-free and serverless backup technology, because some structural integration of IP-based technology, such as iSCSI, especially as future IP storage network storage technology in the possession of strong advantages, LAN- free and serverless backup technology solutions will become more widespread. </p><p> LAN-free and serverless backup is not suitable for all applications. If you have a large data repository to be 7 ÃƒÂ— 24 readily available, no server backup may be a good choice. But must ensure that you have made it clear how long the recovery process, because this will underestimate the face a more serious problem than at the beginning. </p><p> On the other hand, if you have a database of moderate size can tolerate some downtime, then the traditional backup and recovery technology may be your quite good choice. </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' Common data backup systems are Host-Base, LAN-Base Structure-based SAN LAN-Free, Server-Free and other structures.  Host-Based backup:  Host-Based is the traditional structure of the data backup tape library in this structure directly connected to the server, and only data backup service for...'),(159,'Storage','Storage','en','/a/st/2010/0711/303.html','http://www.ixdba.net',' The following information...','_The_following_information','2010-07-11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> The following information easily lead to loss of RAID disk array: <br /> 1. The hard disk in order messed up, causing the boot disk array is not up </p><p> 2. Array disks dropped to two or two more, the collapse of the array </p><p> 3. Expansion of the disk array is not yet complete when the go out into the write data, resulting in the collapse of the array </p><p> 4. Dropped a hard drive, put a good plate Rebuild, cause data is not normal </p><p> 5. Disk physical failure, such as: bad circuit board, heads damage, bad disk, bad sectors, etc. </p><p> 6. In the absence of any exceptional circumstances, the array is not normal boot </p><p> 7. A sudden power outage caused by RAID disk array card information loss </p><p> 8. The hard drive in the wrong order, start the system, or change the configuration; </p><p> If you find raid disk array failure. Please take the following action. </p><p> 1, the system power off, the hard drive in order of number </p><p> 2, will report to the disk array disk array vendor or professional data recovery company </p><p> 3, non-professionals do not try to Rebuild, initialization, synchronization, data recovery attempt to action </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' The following information easily lead to loss of RAID disk array:  1. The hard disk in order messed up, causing the boot disk array is not up  2. Array disks dropped to two or two more, the collapse of the array  3. Expansion of the disk array is not yet complete when the go out into the write...'),(160,'Storage','Storage','en','/a/st/2010/0711/302.html','http://www.ixdba.net',' Following a similar method to...','_Following_a_similar_method_to','2010-07-11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> Following a similar method to test writing ability </p><p><br /> time dd if = / dev / zero of = / oradata / biddb / testind / testfile.dbf bs = 1024000 count = 1000 </p><p><br /> IO can be used during the system (unix): </p><p><br /> iostat-xnp 2 shows the extent Busy </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' Following a similar method to test writing ability  time dd if = / dev / zero of = / oradata / biddb / testind / testfile.dbf bs = 1024000 count = 1000  IO can be used during the system (unix):  iostat-xnp 2 shows the extent Busy  (Editor: South African Ant)...'),(161,'Storage','Storage','en','/a/st/2010/0623/249.html','http://www.ixdba.net',' 1.Target side configuration ...','_1Target_side_configuration_','2010-06-23','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> 1.Target side configuration <br /> end of the target with disk disk array or other hosts. Iscsitarget tool disk space by mapping to the network, initiator side can look to find and use the disk. <br /> Note that a target number of target host can be mapped to the network, which can map multiple block devices to the network. <br /> 1) Package <br /> iscsitarget <br /> From <a href=\"http://sourceforge.net/projects/iscsitarget/files/\">http://sourceforge.net/projects/iscsitarget/files/</a> download the latest version. <br /> 2) compile and install is very simple, unpack, compile, install on the can. <br /> tar zxvf iscsitarget-1.4.19.tar.gz <br /> cd iscsitarget-1.4.19 / <br /> make <br /> make install <br /> The package will iscsitarget kernel module needed, user-level tools, services, startup scripts, configuration files, man manuals installed on your system, including: <br /> iscsi_trgt.ko kernel module <br /> ietd iscsitarget daemon <br /> ietadm iscsitarget the user-level management tools <br /> / Etc / init.d / iscsi-target iscsitarget startup script <br /> / Etc / ietd.conf iscsitarget profile <br /> / Etc / initiators.allow control initiator access to the target. <br /> / Etc / initiators.deny control initiator access to the target. <br /> / Etc / iet / targets.allow been controlling access to different target. <br /> 3) Configure / etc / ietd.conf </p><p> Target iqn.2001-04.com.example: storage.disk2.sys1.xyz <br /> Lun 0 Path = / dev/sda1, Type = fileio <br /> Alias lun0 </p><p> General description: <br /> Target iqn.2001-04.com.example: storage.disk2.sys1.xyz ISCSI Target, said the naming of the same name should be unique within a subnet, the standard naming is: <br /> &quot;Target&quot; + target name (the format is as follows: iqn.yyyy-mm. &lt;reversed Domain name&gt; [: identifier]) <br /> &quot;Lun 0 Path = / dev/sda1&quot; said the block device number is 0, mapped the disk is / dev/sda1. <br /> Type this configuration is set to &quot;fileio&quot;, I mainly used to store a disk share. <br /> Of course, you can set against the need to: &quot;file&quot; or &quot;LVM&quot;. <br /> In addition there are many other parameters can be set, the specific reference: <br /> <a href=\"http://manpages.ubuntu.com/manpages/hardy/man5/ietd.conf.5.html\">http://manpages.ubuntu.com/manpages/hardy/man5/ietd.conf.5.html</a> </p><p> 4) Start iscsitarget <br /> / Etc / init.d / iscsi-target start </p><p> 2.inititor side configuration <br /> 1) Package source package is open-iscsi, rpm package after package, the name iscsi-initiator-utils. <br /> 2) installed the following documents at the main <br /> / Etc / iscsi / iscsid.conf <br /> / Etc / rc.d / init.d / iscsi <br /> / Etc / rc.d / init.d / iscsid <br /> / Sbin / iscsi-iname <br /> / Sbin / iscsiadm <br /> / Sbin / iscsid <br /> / Sbin / iscsistart <br /> / Var / lib / iscsi <br /> / Var / lib / iscsi / ifaces <br /> / Var / lib / iscsi / isns <br /> / Var / lib / iscsi / nodes <br /> / Var / lib / iscsi / send_targets <br /> / Var / lib / iscsi / slp <br /> / Var / lib / iscsi / static <br /> / Var / lock / iscsi </p><p> 3) Connect the target <br /> First, to ensure iscsid daemon started, testing whether a series of operations will fail iscsiadm: <br /> / Etc / init.d / iscsid start </p><p> That target: <br /> iscsiadm-m discovery-t sendtargets-p &lt;iSCSI target ip&gt;: &lt;port&gt; <br /> &lt;port&gt; Is 3260 by default, unless you have a special setting. </p><p> Establish a connection with the target: <br /> iscsiadm-m node-T &lt;target-name&gt;-p &lt;ip-address&gt;: &lt;port&gt; - login <br /> Where target-name target for the previous step found when acquired. </p><p> This time through the fdisk-l can see the map over the disk, the disk can be the same as using the local disk to format, partition and other operations. <br /> Experiment through the following command: <br /> fdisk / dev / sdc <br /> mkfs.ext3 / dev/sdc1 <br /> mount / dev/sdc1 / mnt <br /> dd if = / dev / zero of = 100M.img bs = 1M count = 100 </p><p> 3.target and initiator between the use of CHAP authentication. <br /> CHAP authentication, there are two, one is for the discovery, that if it does not validate the user name and password, they can not initiator side &quot;-m discovery&quot; found in any of the specified host target. <br /> Command will return authentication fails, as follows: <br /> $ Iscsiadm-m discovery-t sendtargets-p 192.168.29.224 <br /> iscsiadm: Login failed to authenticate with target <br /> iscsiadm: discovery login to 192.168.29.224 rejected: initiator error (02/01), non-retryable, giving up </p><p> The other is for the node login, that fruit does not meet the authentication user name and password, can not initiator-side code - login login one on the specified host target. <br /> Command will return authentication fails, as follows: <br /> $ Iscsiadm-m discovery-t sendtargets-p 192.168.29.224 # successfully discover the target on the specified host <br /> 192.168.29.224:3260,1 iqn.2001-04.com.example: storage.disk2.sys1.xyz <br /> $ Iscsiadm-m node-T iqn.2001-04.com.example: storage.disk2.sys1.xyz-p 192.168.29.224 - login # can not be authenticated, the login fails <br /> Logging in to [iface: default, target: iqn.2001-04.com.example: storage.disk2.sys1.xyz, portal: 192.168.29.224,3260] <br /> iscsiadm: Could not login to [iface: default, target: iqn.2001-04.com.example: storage.disk2.sys1.xyz, portal: 192.168.29.224,3260]: <br /> iscsiadm: initiator reported error (15 - already exists) </p><p> 1) In the initiator-side configuration / etc / iscsi / iscsid.conf, add the following options: <br /> # The following three are for the discovery of the. <br /> # Discovery CHAP authentication enabled <br /> discovery.sendtargets.auth.authmethod = CHAP <br /> # Initiator\'s name, it can be other strings, as long as the name of target-side IncomingUse configuration as on the line <br /> discovery.sendtargets.auth.username = iqn.1994-05.com.fedora: ba72af8aaf5 <br /> # Verify the password, and the target side to the same <br /> discovery.sendtargets.auth.password = 1234567890ab </p><p> # Following three is for the login. <br /> Enable CHAP authentication # login <br /> node.session.auth.authmethod = CHAP <br /> # Initiator\'s name, it can be other strings, as long as the name of target-side IncomingUse configuration as on the line <br /> node.session.auth.username = iqn.1994-05.com.fedora: ba72af8aaf5 <br /> # Verify the password, and the target side to the same <br /> node.session.auth.password = 1234567890 </p><p> Then restart initiator. <br /> / Etc / init.d / iscsid stop <br /> / Etc / init.d / iscsid start </p><p> 2) discover the target side fory configure / etc / ietd.conf, at the global parameter (defined before the first target), add the following line: <br /> IncomingUser iqn.1994-05.com.fedora: ba72af8aaf5 1234567890ab <br /> ISCSI IncomingUser and OutgoingUser that the client user name and password, user name and password can be empty, the default permissions to allow the password can be up to 12 characters. <br /> Here iqn.1994-05.com.fedora: ba72af8aaf5 is the initiator name (it can be other strings), 1234567890ab is the initiator of the password, and the initiator name and password must be on the / etc / iscsi / iscsid.conf <br /> User name password in the same. If not, then the initiator implementation of &quot;-m discovery&quot; is will fail. </p><p> For the login configuration / etc / ietd.conf, since it is for the login, then add IncomingUser is to be added on the specified target. As follows: <br /> Target iqn.2001-04.com.example: storage.disk2.sys1.xyz <br /> Lun 0 Path = / dev/sda1, Type = fileio <br /> IncomingUser iqn.1994-05.com.fedora: ba72af8aaf5 1234567890 </p><p> Then restart the iscsitarget <br /> / Etc / init.d / iscsi-target stop <br /> / Etc / init.d / iscsi-target start </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' 1.Target side configuration  end of the target with disk disk array or other hosts. Iscsitarget tool disk space by mapping to the network, initiator side can look to find and use the disk.  Note that a target number of target host can be mapped to the network, which can map multiple block devices...'),(162,'Storage','Storage','en','/a/st/2010/0422/50.html','http://www.ixdba.net',' I: Overview:  DRBD is a...','_I_Overview__DRBD_is_a','2010-04-22','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> I: Overview: </p><p> DRBD is a kernel module and associated scripts and composition, to build high availability clusters. Its implementation is through the network to mirror the entire device. You can see it as a network RAID. Drbd responsible for receiving data, the data written to local disk, and then sent to another host. Another host and then the data stored to your disk. </p><p> Source download <a href=\"http://oss.linbit.com/drbd/0.7/drbd-0.7.19.tar.gz\">http://oss.linbit.com/drbd/0.7/drbd-0.7.19.tar.gz</a> </p><p> Core reference documentation: <a href=\"http://www.drbd.org/drbd-howto.html\">http://www.drbd.org/drbd-howto.html</a> </p><p></p><p> Second: The main implementation </p><p> Suppose there are two machines nannan: 192.168.0.136 need to mirror the hard disk: / dev/hdc3 </p><p> root: 192.168.0.139 need to mirror the hard disk: / dev/hdc2 </p><p> Referred to as the master server is 192.168.0.136 136 </p><p> Referred to as the backup server is 192.168.0.139 139 </p><p> Normal reading and writing of data to achieve in 136, when the 136 down to start after the 139 swap, hot backup data. </p><p> The real needs of the thermal switch was implemented with the HA. </p><p></p><p> Third: Download and install </p><p> Installation Environment: Red Hat Enterprise Linux AS release 4, kernel version :2.6.9-22. EL </p><p> Confirm the existence of the kernel source, can be <a href=\"http://oss.linbit.com/drbd/\">http://oss.linbit.com/drbd/</a> to load. </p><p> Download Source Note: The most current drbd-8.0pre3, configuration files can not be properly configured, there a lot of mistakes, so download the previous stable version. Source unpacked tar </p><p> Run: </p><p> A, make KDIR = / usr / src / linux / * the location of the kernel * / </p><p> / * If you do not change the kernel can run make, the software will go directly to the / lib / module inside to find the system environment, if the new kernel needs to compile the kernel installed </p><p> Otherwise, time will make mistakes and cut off * / </p><p> B, make install </p><p> After installing the main build command: drbdsetup, drbdadmin </p><p> And configuration files: / etc / drbd.conf, startup file, / etc / init.d / drbd </p><p> Module file: drbd.ko (compiled package in the directory can be found under drbd) </p><p> All commands and configuration files can be compiled in the source package directory to find success. </p><p> . / Scripts / drbd.conf is the original configuration file, when the / etc / drbd.conf is damaged, you can copy directly overwritten. </p><p> C, create a hardware device drbd </p><p> mknod / dev/drbd0 b 147 0 </p><p> mknod / dev/drbd1 b 147 1 </p><p> mknod / dev/drbd2 b 147 2 </p><p> Or use the shell to create multiple: </p><p> # For i in $ (seq 0 15); do mknod / dev / drbd $ ib 147 $ i; done </p><p> D, DRBD protocol specification </p><p> A data once written to disk and sent to the network to that the completion of the write operation. </p><p> B received a confirmation to that completed the write operation. </p><p> C receive a written confirmation to that the completion of the write operation. </p><p> You can also choose other parameters to the data to disk and network options. For more information, see drbdsetup man page. </p><p> Four: Configure drbd </p><p> Modify / etc / drbd.conf </p><p> The main changes: the machine name and device name ip address </p><p> ================================================== </p><p> on web1 { </p><p> device / dev/drbd0; </p><p> disk / dev/hdc3; </p><p> address 192.168.0.136:7788; </p><p> meta-disk internal; </p><p> # Meta-disk is either \'internal\' or \'/ dev / ice / name [idx]\' </p><p> # </p><p> # You can use a single block device to store meta-data </p><p> # Of multiple DRBD\'s. </p><p> # Eg use meta-disk / dev/hde6 [0]; and meta-disk / dev/hde6 [1]; </p><p> # For two different resources. In this case the meta-disk </p><p> # Would need to be at least 256 MB in size. </p><p> # </p><p> # \'Internal\' means, that the last 128 MB of the lower device </p><p> # Are used to store the meta-data. </p><p> # You must not give an index with \'internal\'. </p><p> } </p><p> on web2 { </p><p> device / dev/drbd0; </p><p> disk / dev/hdc2; </p><p> address 192.168.0.139:7788; </p><p> meta-disk internal; </p><p> } </p><p> ================================================== </p><p> Here is the drbd.conf profile: </p><p> Note: The configuration version is drbd-0.7.19.tar.gz, different versions are not compatible. The modifications to the above and comments in several places, as well as the outside in addition to resource r0 other configuration blocks, such as resource r1, and all removed. </p><p> That is </p><p> /**** </p><p> on root { </p><p> device / dev/drbd0; </p><p> disk / dev/hdc2; </p><p> address 192.168.0.139:7788; </p><p> meta-disk internal; </p><p> } </p><p> } </p><p> ****/ </p><p> Removed all the contents of all of the back, </p><p></p><p> The following is a complete configured drbd.conf </p><p> # </p><p> # Drbd.conf example </p><p> # </p><p> skip { </p><p> As you can see, you can also comment chunks of text </p><p> with a \'skip [optional nonsense] {skipped text}\' section. </p><p> This comes in handy, if you just want to comment out </p><p> some \'resource &lt;some name&gt; {...}\' section: </p><p> just precede it with \'skip\'. </p><p> The basic format of option assignment is </p><p> &lt;option name&gt; &lt;linear whitespace&gt; &lt;value&gt;; </p><p></p><p> It should be obvious from the examples below, </p><p> but if you really care to know the details: </p><p></p><p> &lt;option name&gt;: = </p><p> valid options in the respective scope </p><p> &lt;value&gt;: = &lt;num&gt; | &lt;string&gt; | &lt;choice&gt; | ... </p><p> depending on the set of allowed values </p><p> for the respective option. </p><p> &lt;num&gt;: = [0-9] +, sometimes with an optional suffix of K, M, G </p><p> &lt;string&gt;: = (&lt;name&gt; | \\ &quot;([^ \\&quot; <a>\\ \\ \\ n] * | \\ \\.) * \\</a> &quot;) + </p><p> &lt;name&gt;: = [/ _.A-Za-z0-9-] + </p><p> } </p><p> # Global { </p><p> # Use this if you want to define more resources later </p><p> # Without reloading the module. </p><p> # By default we load the module with exactly as many devices </p><p> # As configured mentioned in this file. </p><p> # </p><p> # Minor-count 5; </p><p> # The user dialog counts and displays the seconds it waited so </p><p> # Far. You might want to disable this if you have the console </p><p> # Of your server connected to a serial terminal server with </p><p> # Limited logging capacity. </p><p> # The Dialog will print the count each \'dialog-refresh\' seconds, </p><p> # Set it to 0 to disable redrawing completely. [Default = 1] </p><p> # </p><p> # Dialog-refresh 5; # 5 seconds </p><p> # You might disable one of drbdadm\'s sanity check. </p><p> # Disable-ip-verification; </p><p> #} </p><p> # </p><p> # This need not be r #, you may use phony resource names, </p><p> # Like &quot;resource web&quot; or &quot;resource mail&quot;, too </p><p> # </p><p> resource r0 { </p><p> protocol C; </p><p> # What should be done in case the cluster starts up in </p><p> # Degraded mode, but knows it has inconsistent data. </p><p> incon-degr-cmd &quot;echo \'! DRBD! pri on incon-degr\' | wall; sleep 60; halt-f&quot;; </p><p> startup { </p><p> degr-wfc-timeout 120; # 2 minutes. </p><p> } </p><p> disk { </p><p> } </p><p> net { </p><p> } </p><p> syncer { </p><p> rate 10M; </p><p> group 1; </p><p> al-extents 257; </p><p> } </p><p> on web1 { </p><p> device / dev/drbd0; </p><p> disk / dev/hdc3; </p><p> address 192.168.0.136:7788; </p><p> meta-disk internal; </p><p> } </p><p> on web2 { </p><p> device / dev/drbd0; </p><p> disk / dev/hdc2; </p><p> address 192.168.0.139:7788; </p><p> meta-disk internal; </p><p> } </p><p> } </p><p> ================================================= </p><p></p><p> Fifth, start drbd </p><p> Make sure the two machines is normal to the mirror, whether the network between the smooth, hard drive to load the state is in umount. </p><p> A, drbd module is used in a controlled manner </p><p> So first module loaded drbd.ko </p><p> 136 server performs: </p><p> # Insmod drbd.ko or modprobe drbd </p><p> drbd.ko can be found in the compiled source code package. </p><p> Determine whether the load can be used successfully lsmod to see: </p><p> # Lsmod </p><p> Module size Used by </p><p> drbd 143088 - </p><p> Said the success of any load module </p><p> # Drbdadm up all </p><p> Start the drbd service, so he hung in the background running state. </p><p> You can use the command netstat-an see </p><p> Port 7788 has started, but also monitor each other\'s 7788 port to achieve data exchange. </p><p> the output of netstat-ant in one line: </p><p> # Netstat-ant </p><p> tcp 0 0 192.168.0.136:7789 0.0.0.0: * LISTEN </p><p></p><p> B: In the implementation of 139 servers </p><p> # Modprobe drbd </p><p> # / Etc / rc.d / init.d / drbd start </p><p> the output of netstat-atn, indicating that the two virtual machines have been connected to the drbd service: </p><p> # Netstat-ant </p><p> tcp 0 0 192.168.0.136:7789 192.168.0.139:32845 ESTABLISHED </p><p> tcp 0 0 192.168.0.136:32770 192.168.0.139:7789 ESTABLISHED </p><p> Six: Set permissions </p><p> drbd up basic services, and now the server will need to master the 192.168.0.136 to configure this server so that he can read and write drbd0 equipment. </p><p> Machine running at 136 </p><p> # Drbdadm - - do-what-I-say primary all # set the home directory synchronization server 136, which is synchronized to 136 of the partition shall prevail. </p><p> Note that the command format, as required, without any hints as saying that basically the success </p><p> # Sfdisk-s </p><p> Can see there is a hardware device: / dev/drbd0 </p><p> At this point, between the two devices to establish a mirror, you can view / proc / drbd verify. </p><p> # Cat / proc / drbd </p><p> If the original hard disk file system is not the case, you can now device / dev/drbd0 create a file system and then loaded into the 136 on it. </p><p> # Mkfs.ext3-j / dev/drbd0 </p><p> # Mkdir / mnt / gaojf </p><p> # Mount / dev / drbd / mnt / gaojf </p><p> Now / dev/drbd0 your server above is equivalent to a hardware device, you can read and write any of his operations. </p><p> Seven: drbd test: </p><p> 1: 136 on the master server: </p><p> # Drbdadm primary all </p><p> # Touch / mnt / gaojf / gaojf </p><p> After the implementation of </p><p> # Umount / mnt / gaojf </p><p> # Drbdadm secondary all </p><p> 2: Next to the implementation of the standby server 139 </p><p> # Drbdadm primary all </p><p> # Mkdir-p / mnt / gaojf </p><p> # Mount / dev/drbd0 / mnt / gaojf </p><p> # Ls-l / mnt / gaojf / gaojf </p><p> gaojf </p><p> Ok, no problem, you can see the data is written in 136 servers, can be seen immediately at 139. </p><p></p><p> Some caveats: </p><p> 1. Mount drbd device before the device must switch to the primary state. </p><p> 2. Two nodes, the same time, only one in a primary state, another state in the secondary. </p><p> 3. In a secondary state can not load the drbd device on the server. </p><p> 4. Main and backup server, the best synchronization of the two partitions the same size, so as not to waste disk space, because the drbd disk image equivalent to the network raid 1. </p><p> 5: During the configuration process, if there is the following error </p><p> Missing argument \'meta_data_dev\' </p><p> USAGE: </p><p> disk lower_dev meta_data_dev meta_data_index [{- size |-d} 0 ... 8587575296] </p><p> [{- On-io-error |-e} {pass_on | call-local-io-error | detach}] </p><p> [{- Fencing |-f} {dont-care | resource-only | resource-and-stonith}] [{- use-bmbv |-b}] </p><p> Then you have to initialize meta-data area </p><p> drbdadm create-md r0 </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' I: Overview:  DRBD is a kernel module and associated scripts and composition, to build high availability clusters. Its implementation is through the network to mirror the entire device. You can see it as a network RAID. Drbd responsible for receiving data, the data written to local disk, and then...'),(163,'Cluster Technology','Load_Balancing','en','/a/lb/2010/0920/766.html','http://www.ixdba.net','A cluster definition Cluster...','A_cluster_definition_Cluster','2010-09-20','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><strong>A <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/lb/\">cluster</a></u> definition</strong> <br /> Cluster is a group work set of services, to provide more stable than a single service, more efficient, more scalable platform, the outside, the cluster is an independent service entity, but in fact, in the cluster Internally, there are two or more entities in the coordination of services, with the completion of a complex task. <br /> Clusters of two or more generally formed from a server, each server is called a cluster node, the cluster nodes can communicate with each other, communicate in two ways, one is based on the RS232 line heart rate monitor, Another is to use a separate card to run the heartbeat, therefore, the cluster service with the state monitoring function between the nodes, but also must have the extension service entities, the flexibility to add and remove a service entity. <br /> In the cluster, the same services can be provided by multiple service entities. Thus, when a node fails, another node in the cluster automatically take over the failed node\'s resources to ensure service lasting, uninterrupted operation. Thus the transfer function of the cluster with automatic fault. <br /> A cluster must have a shared data storage, because the services provided outside the cluster is the same, any one cluster node to run an application, the application of the data are centrally stored in the node shared space, and the operating system on each node only running application services, application files stored. <br /> In summary, to build a cluster system requires at least two servers, but also need to have the serial line, cluster software, shared storage devices (such as disk arrays) and so on. <br /> Based <a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/linux/\"><u>Linux</u></a> cluster with its very high computing power, scalability, availability and more cost-effective optimization of a variety of applications in the enterprise to stand out. Become a concern for all <a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/linux/\"><u>Linux</u></a> applications hot, master knowledge of Linux clusters, low price can be used to make high-performance applications. To enterprises and individuals to save costs. Large domestic Sina, Netease, adopted high-performance linux cluster building web applications, using the famous search engine google linux servers on a million, a large cluster, the cluster of these instances shows the status of the application in linux and important sex. <br /> <strong>Features and functions of the cluster 2</strong> <br /> 2.1 High availability and scalability <br /> 1. High availability for some very strong real-time applications, must ensure that the service runs 24 hours a day, and as software, hardware, network, human and other reasons, a single service operating environment difficult to meet this requirement at this time build a cluster system is a good choice to build one of the greatest advantages of the cluster with high availability cluster, the service fails, the cluster system can automatically switch the service from the failed node to another backup node to provide uninterrupted service, ensure the continued operation of the business. <br /> 2. Scalability with the increasing volume of business, the existing entity can not meet the needs of the cluster service, you can dynamically to the cluster, add one or more service nodes, to meet application needs, and enhance the overall performance of the cluster. This is the scalability of the cluster. <br /> 2.2 load balancing and error recovery <br /> 1. Load balancing cluster system is characterized by the greatest flexibility, and effective sharing of system load, defined by the cluster load sharing their own strategies, allocation of the client\'s access to the following each service node, for example, you can define polling allocation strategy, the average request allocation to each service node, you can also define the minimum load allocation strategy, when a request comes in, determine which service node cluster system are relatively free to distribute this request to this node. <br /> 2. Error recovery when a node in a task not yet complete, for some reason fails, time, and then another service node should be able to accomplish this task, which is the cluster to provide error recovery, through error redirection to ensure that each mission can be effectively completed. <br /> 2.3 IP heartbeat detection and drift <br /> 1. Heart rate monitoring in order to achieve load balancing, providing high availability services and the implementation of error recovery, the cluster system provides the heartbeat monitoring, heart rate monitoring is achieved through the heartbeat, the heartbeat of the equipment can do a RS 232 serial line can also be used independently heartbeat to run a piece of card can also be a shared disk arrays, the number of heartbeat cluster nodes should be decreased by 1, note that if the heartbeat through the card to do so, each node has two network cards, of which a private network as the machine is connected directly to each other the appropriate card, to monitor each heartbeat. Also a connection to the outside public network to provide services, while heart rate card and IP card services, as not in a subnet address. Direct impact on the efficiency of the heart rate monitor the duration of failover, the cluster system is maintained through the heart technology and effective communication between nodes inside. <br /> 2. Drift IP address in the cluster system, in addition to each service node itself the real IP address, IP address there is a drift, then why is the drift IP, because the IP addresses are not fixed, for example, double the two nodes hot standby, the normal state, the drift of IP in the master node, when the primary node fails, the drift IP address automatically switches to the standby node, therefore, in order to ensure uninterrupted service in the cluster system, external provision of services IP must be to the drift IP address, although the IP node itself can also offer services, but when the node failure, the service switched to another node, but the service failed node IP is still IP address, this time, the service with the interrupt.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><strong>Category 3 Cluster <br /></strong> 3.1 High Availability Cluster <br /> 1. The concept of high availability in English stands for High Availability Cluster High Availability Cluster, referred to as HA Cluster, the maximum availability of the means available, from the name of the cluster can be seen, the function of these Clusters is to protect the user\'s application program lasting, uninterrupted service. <br /> When an application fails, or the system hardware, network failure, the application can automatically, quickly switching from one node to another node, in order to ensure application of sustained, uninterrupted service outside, which is to achieve high-availability clustering functions <br /> 2. Common HA Cluster <br /> We often say that the hot standby, dual-prepared, multi-machine equipment and so on are each other\'s areas of high availability clusters, these clusters typically have two or more nodes. A typical hot standby structure shown in Figure 1:</span></span> </p><div style=\"text-align: center\"> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" height=\"182\" onclick=\"window.open(&apos;/uploads/allimg/100920/1_100920093219_1.png&apos;)\" src=\"http://www.ixdba.net/uploads/allimg/100920/1_100920093219_1.png\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" width=\"384\" /><br /><br /> Figure 1 Structure of Hot Standby</span></span> </div><p> <span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Hot Standby mode is the simplest application, that is often said that the active / standby mode, it uses two servers, one as the master server (action), run the application outside service, the other as a standby machine (standby ), installation and application as the main server, but did not start the service, is in the standby state. Between the host and prepare machine technology with each other through the heartbeat monitoring, monitoring of the resources can be network, operating system, and also the service, the user can according to your needs, choose the resources need to be monitored, when monitoring and controlling equipment to host a resource failure, according to a predetermined strategy, first IP switch over, then the application services are taken over, and then to provide services outside the preparation unit, the switching time is end of the process, users simply do not feel out of the program issues, but also for the switching, in order to protect the application lasting, uninterrupted service. <br /> Dual Active in hot standby, based on two independent applications to run simultaneously on two machines, Internet-based equipment, which is prepared by two servers both host machine, when any one application fails, another server in a short time can be taken over the application of machine malfunction, in order to protect the service continued, uninterrupted operation. Dual Active advantage is saving equipment resources, the two hot standby application requires at least four servers, and Dual Active only two servers to complete high-availability clustering capabilities, but also have Dual Active the shortcomings of its own: in a node failover, another node to run the two applications to the service, there may be the case load is too large. <br /> Preparation of multi-machine interaction is a hot standby of the technology upgrade, through a cluster composed of multiple machines can be set up between multiple machines over a flexible strategy, for example, a server cluster environment composed of 8, 3 runs web applications, 3 applications to run mail, therefore, the remaining one can be as prepared 3 sets of web server machines, 3 sets another mail server as a reserve unit, through such arrangements, adequate and reasonable use of the server resources, but also to ensure the system\'s high availability. <br /> Note that: high-availability cluster can not guarantee the security of application data, it is only lasting solution is to provide uninterrupted service of external, to the software, hardware, networking, human factors failures reduce the impact of the application to the lowest level. <br /> 3. High Availability Cluster high-availability cluster software is generally achieved through the high-availability software, commonly used in high availability under linux software: open source heartbea HA, Redhat provides RHCS, business software ROSE, keepalived and so on. In the following sections we will detail heartbea HA configuration and use. <br /> 3.2 Load Balancing Load balancing system, the English full name Load Balance Cluster, referred to as LB Cluster, the load balancing cluster also has two or more than two servers, divided into front end and back-end node services load scheduling of two parts, the load scheduling partially responsible for the client\'s request in accordance with the policies assigned to different back-end service node, and back-end nodes is the real part of providing application services. <br /> The difference is that with HA Cluster in the load balancing cluster, all the back-end nodes are active, they offer services, work load sharing system. <br /> Load balancing cluster can be applied to a high load across multiple nodes to jointly complete for the busy business, access to a large load applications, but it also has deficiencies: When a node fails, the front-end dispatch system does not that this node can no longer provide services, will continue to dispatch client requests to the failed node up, so that access will fail, in order to solve this problem, the load scheduling system generally introduces a node monitoring system. <br /> Node monitoring system is located on the front-end load dispatcher responsible for monitoring the following service node, when a node fails, the node monitor</span></span>Failed node will automatically be removed from the cluster, when the node is back to normal, the node monitoring system will automatically add it to the cluster, all of this, the user is completely transparent. <br /> Figure 2 shows the basic structure of the cluster load balancing: <br /></p><div style=\"text-align: center\"> <span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" height=\"278\" onclick=\"window.open(&apos;/uploads/allimg/100920/1_100920093137_1.png&apos;)\" src=\"http://www.ixdba.net/uploads/allimg/100920/1_100920093137_1.png\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" width=\"536\" /><br /> Figure 2, the basic framework of the cluster load balancing</span></span> </div><p style=\"text-align: left\"> <span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Load balancing cluster can be achieved by software can also be done by the hardware, linux software under a typical load balancing: LVS cluster open source, Oracle\'s RAC cluster, etc., hardware load balancers such as F5 Networks have. About LVS cluster, in the following chapters we will explain in detail. <br /> 3.3 High Performance Computing Science Computing Cluster (High Perfermance Computing) clusters, referred to as HPC clusters. Such clustering is committed to providing a single computer can provide a powerful computing capabilities, including numerical computation and data processing, and tend to the pursuit of overall performance. HPC and supercomputing is similar, but there are different, the calculation speed is the first goal of the pursuit of super-computing. The fastest speed, maximum storage, the volume of the largest and most expensive prices represent the characteristics of supercomputing, as people demand to improve computing speed, super-computing is also applied to various fields of supercomputing speed pursuit of a single calculation the pursuit of performance indicators into composite indicators. The high performance computing. <br /> A wide range of HPC applications, typical applications include: life science research, genetic testing comparison, data mining, oil and gas exploration, image rendering and so on. <br /></span></span> </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>','A cluster definition Cluster is a group work set of services, to provide more stable than a single service, more efficient, more scalable platform, the outside, the cluster is an independent service entity, but in fact, in the cluster Internally, there are two or more entities in the coordination of...'),(164,'Cluster Technology','Load_Balancing','en','/a/lb/2010/0711/301.html','http://www.ixdba.net',' Database dual hot with two...','_Database_dual_hot_with_two','2010-07-11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> Database dual hot with two typical methods for a standard of comparison, the two servers via a shared storage device (usually a shared disk array or storage area network SAN), and install the software, double, dual hot standby, known as the shared way. Another way is through pure software approach, commonly referred to as pure software or in mirror mode (Mirror). </p><p> For shared mode, the database on a shared storage device. When a server provides services directly in the storage device to read and write. When the system switch, another server also reads the data on the storage device. </p><p> For pure software approach, through the mirroring software, the data can be copied to another server in real time, so that the same data on the existence of a two servers, if one server fails, you can switch to another time servers. </p><p> Pure software approach to a certain extent, reduce costs, but it also has very significant disadvantages: </p><p> 1. Reliability is relatively poor, the two real-time replication of data between servers is a relatively weak link. </p><p> 2. Once a server interruption, even after the resumption for more sophisticated data synchronization recovery. And, this time the system is not protected. </p><p> 3. There is no transaction mechanism, because of its replication is in the file and disk layer, and copy the database transaction will not affect the success of operations, it is a complete change of data is not the case, there is considerable risk in this. </p><p> Therefore, it is recommended unless a last resort, do not choose a software program. </p><p> On the other hand, there is a parallel database solution, it is not in the file or to copy the disk layer, but directly on the database front-end routing in the distribution operation, in parallel to complete the database update transaction mechanism, but also can provide the database parallel service. In this way the current application for SQL SERVER very successful, much better than shared memory mode + dual machine software </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' Database dual hot with two typical methods for a standard of comparison, the two servers via a shared storage device (usually a shared disk array or storage area network SAN), and install the software, double, dual hot standby, known as the shared way. Another way is through pure software approach,...'),(165,'Cluster Technology','Load_Balancing','en','/a/lb/2010/0711/300.html','http://www.ixdba.net','ITPUB see in such a case, in a...','ITPUB_see_in_such_a_case_in_a','2010-07-11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">ITPUB see in such a case, in a set of <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/linux/\">Linux</a></u> in the RAC environment, an OCFS volume inode node has been used, but the database still running. <br /> Files can be properly created, the <a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/os/\"><u>system</u></a> of several conditions as follows:</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">OS: LINUXAS3 U3 <br /> ORACLE: ORACLE9204 RAC</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">The following is the specific show, / U04 produce only two-node storage of archive log</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">[Root @ db1 /] # cat / etc / issue <br /> Red Hat Enterprise Linux AS release 3 (Taroon Update 3)</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">[Root @ db1 /] # rpm-qa | grep ocfs <br /> ocfs-support-1.0.10-1 <br /> ocfs-tools-1.0.10-1 <br /> ocfs-2.4.21-EL-smp-1.0.13-1</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">[Root @ db1 /] # df-h <br /> Filesystem Size Used Avail Use% Mounted on <br /> / Dev/emcpowerd1 50G 44M 50G 1% / u04</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">[Root @ db1 /] # df-i <br /> Filesystem Inodes IUsed IFree IUse% Mounted on <br /> / Dev/emcpowerd1 409580 409231 349 100% / u04</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\"><br /> Finally, the author found an explanation from Metalink, that OCFS file system and is usually different, inodes are not here to play the role of the file system normally. <br /> This is the characteristics of OCFS, it is normal.</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">References that explain the record as follows:</span></span> </p><p> <span style=\"font-family: Tahoma\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">@ OCFS does not have the concept of inodes, however, for the vfs layer in the <br /> @ Kernel we need to fill out structures. The number returned by df-i is <br /> @ Based on diskspace free. It\'s the number of clusterblocsk in the filesystem <br /> @ We dont \'preallocate inodes like most filesystems do. Nor do we HAVE to do <br /> @ That. Not a bug, expected behaviour, not required to do what any other <br /> @ Filesystem does. <br /></span></span> </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>','ITPUB see in such a case, in a set of Linux in the RAC environment, an OCFS volume inode node has been used, but the database still running.  Files can be properly created, the system of several conditions as follows:OS: LINUXAS3 U3  ORACLE: ORACLE9204 RACThe following is the specific show, / U04...'),(166,'Cluster Technology','Load_Balancing','en','/a/lb/2010/0711/299.html','http://www.ixdba.net',' SteelEye\'s LifeKeeper the...','_SteelEyes_LifeKeeper_the','2010-07-11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> SteelEye\'s LifeKeeper the United States is supporting a variety of soft (WindowNT, Windows2000, various Linux, etc.), high-performance fault-tolerant hardware platform, software can support up to 16 servers <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/lb/\">clustered</a></u> . Lifekeeper software from NCR Corporation and the leading U.S. AT &amp; T Bell Labs. For enterprises, banks and government information services, business services, government services, providing high availability solutions. </p><p> LifeKeeper high availability fault-tolerant cluster software is running on NT, Windows 2000, Linux and NCR Unix platforms. Way to support both software-mirrored disk array cabinets and shared approach and real-time replication to support remote disaster backup and recovery system. So that the user\'s servers, operating systems, database systems and critical data and applications to keep 7 days ÃƒÂ— 24 hours of continuous uninterrupted, providing 99.99% availability. Software includes a number of core parts and for different applications ARK. </p><p> The key features of LifeKeeper </p><p><br /> 1. Without any additional investment in hardware, pure software approach to achieve Fault-tolerant, and to the preparation machine without hardware configuration requirements. <br /><br /> 2. Support for Notes, Exchange, SQL Server, Sybase, Informix, Oracle, SAP and other application-level heat recovery system. <br /><br /> 3. Is the world\'s first set of NT-based operating system supports fault-tolerant software and LINUX platforms. Remote disaster recovery. <br /><br /> 4. Support the expansion of shared disk array cabinets and mirrors in two ways, give users the flexibility to choose, but also to adapt to a variety of models, network architecture, software platforms and applications. <br /><br /> 5. LifeKeeper in shared disk array mirrored or extended any way, can achieve two servers running different applications and their mutual hot backup, the dual Active operation mode. <br /><br /> 6. Shared disk array cabinet mode, can support up to 16 nodes, much larger than other similar systems are supported by two nodes. <br /><br /> 7. Maximize the protection of the client application continuity. The user\'s hardware resources (such as network cards), software resources (such as the NT operating system, database management systems, database applications, e-mail systems, etc.) can in under LifeKeeper protection, conservation of resources when these are a technical failure, LifeKeeper implementation of system resources can be switched at any time. So, LifeKeeper truly a user\'s hardware or software failure of the system resources and application-layer switch on the hot line. <br /><br /> 8. LifeKeeper minimal system resources, without increasing network load, and do not disturb any specific application of any operation. <br /><br /> 9. LifeKeeper truly unattended, automatic application of resources to achieve change, and the graphics interface operation, simple and convenient. <br /><br /> 10. Since put into use, has undergone a large number of transactions the actual peak of the test, its implementation is very efficient and reliable operation, the global market share first. <br /></p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' SteelEye\'s LifeKeeper the United States is supporting a variety of soft (WindowNT, Windows2000, various Linux, etc.), high-performance fault-tolerant hardware platform, software can support up to 16 servers clustered . Lifekeeper software from NCR Corporation and the leading U.S. AT & T Bell Labs....'),(167,'Cluster Technology','Load_Balancing','en','/a/lb/2010/0711/298.html','http://www.ixdba.net',' Ipvsadm command of reference,...','_Ipvsadm_command_of_reference','2010-07-11','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> Ipvsadm command of reference, and used according to their own experience, for a simple translation, in the hope ipvsadm will certainly help users. In order to better enable us to understand the commands manual, which the manual a few terms used in the first brief look: <br /> 1, virtual-service-address: is the ip address of the virtual server <br /> 2, real-service-address: refers to the real server ip address <br /> 3, scheduler: Scheduling </p><p><br /> ipvsadm usage and format are as follows: <br /> QUOTE: <br /> ipvsadm-A | E-t | u | f virutal-service-address: port [-s scheduler] [-p <br /> [Timeout]] [-M netmask] <br /> ipvsadm-D-t | u | f virtual-service-address <br /> ipvsadm-C <br /> ipvsadm-R <br /> ipvsadm-S [-n] <br /> ipvsadm-a | e-t | u | f service-address: port-r real-server-address: port <br /> [-G | i | m] [-w weight] <br /> ipvsadm-d-t | u | f service-address-r server-address <br /> ipvsadm-L | l [options] <br /> ipvsadm-Z [-t | u | f service-address] <br /> ipvsadm - set tcp tcpfin udp <br /> ipvsadm - start-daemon state [- mcast-interface interface] <br /> ipvsadm - stop-daemon <br /> ipvsadm-h </p><p> Command options explained: </p><p> There are two command-option format, long and short, has the same meaning. In actual use, the two can be. <br /> -A - add-service virtual server table in the kernel to add a new virtual server records. Is adding a new virtual server. <br /> -E - edit-service edit the kernel virtual server table in a virtual server record. <br /> -D - delete-service Delete the kernel virtual server table in a virtual server record. <br /> -C - clear clear kernel virtual server table all records. <br /> -R - restore restore virtual server rules <br /> -S - save to save the virtual server rules for the-R option readable output format <br /> -A - add-server virtual server table in the kernel to add a record a new record of the real server. That is, in a virtual server, add a new real server <br /> -E - edit-server editing a virtual server records in the record on a particular real server <br /> -D - delete-server virtual server to delete a record in the record on a particular real server <br /> -L |-l - list Display the kernel virtual server table <br /> -Z - zero virtual service table counter is cleared (clear the current number of connections, etc.) <br /> - Set tcp tcpfin udp set the connection timeout value <br /> - Start-daemon start the synchronization daemon. Behind him can be a master or backup, to illustrate the LVS Router is the master or backup. In this function can also be used keepalived the VRRP functionality. </p><p> - Stop-daemon stop synchronization daemon <br /> -H - help Display help information <br /> -T - tcp-service service-address that the virtual server services are tcp <br /> [Vip: port] or [real-server-ip: port] <br /> -U - udp-service service-address that the virtual server service is udp <br /> [Vip: port] or [real-server-ip: port] <br /> -F - fwmark-service fwmark that is marked by the type of service iptables. <br /> -S - scheduler scheduler using the scheduling algorithm, have several options <br /> rr | wrr | lc | wlc | lblc | lblcr | dh | sh | sed | nq, <br /> The default scheduling algorithm is: </p><p> wlc. <br /> -P - persistent [timeout] persistent services. This option means that many times from the same client request will be handled the same real server. The default timeout is 300 seconds. <br /> -M - netmask netmask persistent granularity mask </p><p> -R - real-server server-address the real server [Real-Server: port] <br /> -G - gatewaying specify the operating mode for the LVS direct routing mode (default mode is LVS) <br /> -I - ipip LVS working mode specified tunnel mode <br /> -M - masquerading as the designated working mode of LVS NAT mode <br /> -W - weight weight weight real server <br /> - Mcast-interface interface specifies the synchronization interface to multicast <br /> -C - connection shows the current connection, such as LVS: ipvsadm-L-c <br /> - Timeout show timeout tcp tcpfin udp\'s value as: ipvsadm-L - timeout <br /> - Daemon daemon status display synchronization <br /> - Stats show statistics <br /> - Rate display rate information <br /> - Sort of virtual servers and sort out the real server <br /> - Numeric-n output IP address and port number of the form </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' Ipvsadm command of reference, and used according to their own experience, for a simple translation, in the hope ipvsadm will certainly help users. In order to better enable us to understand the commands manual, which the manual a few terms used in the first brief look:  1, virtual-service-address:...'),(168,'Cluster Technology','Load_Balancing','en','/a/lb/2010/0610/200.html','http://www.ixdba.net',' Configuration before the...','_Configuration_before_the','2010-06-10','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> Configuration before the application of preparatory work before the cluster in the configuration of the cluster configuration information has a good design, the following is the configuration of our cluster information: <br /> Different machines on the same network segment configured on the cluster, the following is based on two machines to do clustering, <br /> Machine type operating system, hardware configuration notes the role of an ordinary PC Linux as 4 IP: 10.3.15.85 PORT: 9080 Managed Server Pc1 <br /> Common PC Linux as 4 IP: 10.3.15.84 PORT: 9080 Managed Server Pc2 <br /> Common PC Linux as 4 IP: 10.3.15.85 PORT: 80 Balancer Server Pc1 <br /><br /> 1 operating system <br /> RedHat Linux as4 <br /> 2 Required Software <br /> Apache 2.0.54 Download <br /> http://apache.freelamp.com/httpd/httpd-2.0.54.tar.gz <br /> Tomcat5.5.9 Download <br /> http://apache.justdn.org/jakarta/ <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/web/tomcat/\">Tomcat</a></u> -5/v5.5.9/bin/jakarta- <u><a href=\"http://www.ixdba.net/a/web/tomcat/\">Tomcat</a></u> -5.5.9.tar.gz <br /> Mod_jk 1.2.14 Download <br /> http://apache.justdn.org/jakarta/tomcat-connectors/jk/source/jk-1.2.14/jakarta-tomcat-connectors-1.2.14-src.tar.gz <br /> Jdk 1_5_0_04 Download <br /> http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.5.0/download.jsp <br /> Note: Download the package file will be required in the / usr / local directory, you can also use jdk1.4 <br /> 3 Installation Steps <br /> Install JDK 3.1 <br /> # Cd / usr / local / <br /> # Chmod 777 jdk-1_5_0_04-linux-i586-rpm.bin <br /> # ./jdk-1.5.0_04-linux-i586-rpm.bin <br /> # Cd / usr / java / <br /> # Ln-s / usr/java/jdk-1_5_0_04 / usr / local / java <br /> # Vi / etc / profile <br /> # Add the following <br /> JAVA_HOME = / usr / local / java / <br /> CLASSPATH = / usr / local / java / lib / dt.jar: / usr / local / java / lib / tools.jar <br /> PATH = / usr / local / java / bin: $ PATH <br /> export PATH JAVA_HOME CLASSPATH <br /><br /> Installing Apache 3.2 <br /> # Cd / usr / local / <br /> # Tar xvfz httpd-2.0.54.tar.gz <br /> # Cd httpd-2.0.54 <br /> #. / Configure-prefix = / usr / local / apache-enable-module = so <br /> # Make <br /> # Make install <br /> # Cd / usr / local / apache / conf <br /> # Vi. / Httpd.conf <br /> Listen 80 will be modified to Listen &lt;Your IP&gt;: 80 <br /> Will be revised ServerName ServerName &lt;HOST-NAME&gt;: 80 <br /> Add in the DirectoryIndex index.jsp <br /> # Cd / usr / local / apache / bin / <br /> #. / Apachectl configtest <br /> If the display indicates a successful installation Syntax ok <br /> #. / Apachectl start <br /> Start the apache service, access to port 80 of the machine to see whether the normal port <br /> #. / Apachectl stop <br /> Close Services Note: prefix defined in the installation path of apache <br /><br /> Install Tomcat 3.3 <br /> # Cd / usr / local / <br /> # Tar xvfz jakarta-tomcat-5.5.9.tar.gz <br /> # Ln-s / usr/local/jakarta-tomcat-5.5.9 / usr / local / tomcat <br /> # Vi / usr / local / tomcat / bin / catalina.sh <br /> JAVA_HOME = / usr / local / java <br /> Start the service, access to the local 8080 port, see the port is normal <br /> # / Usr / local / tomcat / bin / startup.sh / startup.bat <br /> Close Service <br /> # / Usr / local / tomcat / bin / shutdown.sh / shutdown.bat <br /> 3.4 Installation JK <br /> # Cd / usr / local / <br /> # Tar xzvf jakarta-tomcat-connectors-1.2.14-src.tar.gz <br /> # Cd jakarta-tomcat-connectors-1.2.14-src/jk/native <br /> # Chmod 755 buildconf.sh <br /> #. / Buildconf.sh <br /> #. / Configure-with-apxs = / usr / local / apache / bin / apxs <br /> # Make <br /> # Make install <br /> # Cd / usr / local / jakarta-tomcat-connectors-jk1.2.14-src/jk/native/apache-2.0 / <br /> # Cp mod_jk.so / usr / local / apache / modules / <br /><br /> 4 System Integration <br /> 4.1 at the end of the file add the following statements best <br /> # Vi / usr / local / apache / conf / httpd.conf <br /><br /> # Load mod_jk <br /> LoadModule jk_module modules / mod_jk.so <br /> # Configure mod_jk <br /> JkWorkersFile conf / workers.properties <br /> JkLogFile logs / mod_jk.log <br /> JkLogLevel info <br /> JkMount / *. jsp loadbalancer <br /> JkMount / servlet / * loadbalancer <br /> JkMount / application / * loadbalancer <br /><br /> Add workers.properties 4.2 <br /> # Vi / usr / local / apache / conf / workers.properties <br /> As follows: <br /><br /> worker.list = loadbalancer <br /> # Define a \'local_worker\' worker using ajp13 <br /> worker.worker1.port = 8009 <br /> worker.worker1.host = 10.3.15.84 <br /> worker.worker1.type = ajp13 <br /> worker.worker1.lbfactor = 1 <br /> worker.worker1.local_worker = 0 <br /> worker.worker1.cachesize = 1000 <br /> worker.worker1.cache_timeout = 600 <br /> worker.worker1.socket_keepalive = 1 <br /> worker.worker1.socket_timeout = 0 <br /> worker.worker1.reclycle_timeout = 300 <br /> worker.worker1.retries = 3 <br /><br /> # Define another \'local_worker\' worker using ajp13 <br /> worker.worker2.port = 8009 <br /> worker.worker2.host = 10.3.15.85 <br /> worker.worker2.type = ajp13 <br /> worker.worker2.lbfactor = 1 <br /> worker.worker2.local_worker = 1 <br /> worker.worker2.cachesize = 1000 <br /> worker.worker2.cache_timeout = 600 <br /> worker.worker2.socket_keepalive = 1 <br /> worker.worker2.socket_timeout = 0 <br /> worker.worker1.reclycle_timeout = 300 <br /> worker.worker1.retries = 3 <br /><br /> # Define the LB worker <br /> worker.loadbalancer.type = lb <br /> worker.loadbalancer.balanced_workers = worker1, worker2 <br /> worker.loadbalancer.local_worker_only = 1 <br /> worker.loadbalancer.sticky_session = true <br /> worker.loadbalancer.sticky_session_force = true <br /><br /> Note: The above defines two worker, one for worker1, the other is worker2, defines a load balancing server loadbalancer, which focus on standard configuration items in blue, the associated detailed description of the document can see the official website: http:/ / tomcat.apache.org / connectors-doc / <br /><br /> worker.list = loadbalancer <br /> Set the work load balancers, the Tomcat node can not join this list. <br /> worker.worker1.lbfactor <br /> Load balancing weight ratio greater than if the weight is assigned to this node, the request more than two nodes, such as the weight ratio of 1:1, compared with the average distribution. <br /> worker.loadbalancer.balance_workers = worker1, worker2 <br /> Specify the load balancer is responsible for the Tomcat Application node. <br /> worker.loadbalancer.sticky_session = true <br /> Here you can specify whether the cluster session replication, if set to true, indicates that the viscosity for the session, without session replication, when a user requests units where the first distribution of Tomcat, the subsequent distribution of this request will have on the Tomcat server treatment; If set to false, it indicates that demand for session replication. <br /> worker.loadbalancer.sticky_session_force = true <br /> If the above sticky_session set to true, it is suggested here is also set to true, the argument that if a machine in the cluster Tomcat server does not respond after repeated requests, whether the current request, forwarded to another Tomcat server processing; this parameters sticky_session = true, the impact is relatively large, will lead to other Tomcat server forwards the request could not find the original session, so if there is a request at this time to read some of the information session, it would cause the application of null exception. <br /><br /> 4.3 Modify server.xml <br /> # Vi / usr / local / tomcat / conf / server.xml <br /> Around line 120 add the following statement <br /> &lt;Engine Name=&quot;Standalone&quot; defaultHost=&quot;localhost&quot; jvmRoute=&quot;tomcat1&quot;&gt; &lt;/ Engine&gt; <br /> If the second worker1, will be modified as worker2 jvmRoute <br /> And released the following cluster configuration, which is removed comments. <br /> &lt;Cluster className = &quot;org.apache.catalina.cluster.tcp.SimpleTcpCluster&quot; <br /> managerClassName = &quot;org.apache.catalina.cluster.session.DeltaManager&quot; <br /> expireSessionsOnShutdown = &quot;false&quot; <br /> useDirtyFlag = &quot;true&quot;&gt; <br /><br /> &lt;Membership <br /> className = &quot;org.apache.catalina.cluster.mcast.McastService&quot; <br /> mcastAddr = &quot;228.0.0.4&quot; <br /> mcastPort = &quot;45564&quot; <br /> mcastFrequency = &quot;500&quot; <br /> mcastDropTime = &quot;3000&quot; /&gt; <br /><br /> &lt;Receiver <br /> className = &quot;org.apache.catalina.cluster.tcp.ReplicationListener&quot; <br /> tcpListenAddress = &quot;10.3.15.85&quot; <br /> tcpListenPort = &quot;4001&quot; <br /> tcpSelectorTimeout = &quot;100&quot; <br /> tcpThreadCount = &quot;6&quot; /&gt; <br /><br /> &lt;Sender <br /> className = &quot;org.apache.catalina.cluster.tcp.ReplicationTransmitter&quot; <br /> replicationMode = &quot;pooled&quot; /&gt; <br /> &lt;Valve className = &quot;org.apache.catalina.cluster.tcp.ReplicationValve&quot; <br /> filter = &quot;.* \\. gif; .* \\. js; .* \\. jpg; .* \\. htm; .* \\. html; .* \\. txt;&quot; /&gt; <br /> &lt;Deployer className = &quot;org.apache.catalina.cluster.deploy.FarmWarDeployer&quot; <br /> tempDir = &quot;/ tmp / war-temp /&quot; <br /> deployDir = &quot;/ tmp / war-deploy /&quot; <br /> watchDir = &quot;/ tmp / war-listen /&quot; <br /> watchEnabled = &quot;false&quot; /&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Cluster&gt; <br /><br /> At this point, the entire system has been completed and start the apache tomcat service <br /> # / Usr / local / apache / bin / apachectl start <br /> # / Usr / local / tomcat / bin / catalina.sh start <br /> Add the following to / etc / rc.d / rc.local end of the file to open after system startup apache, tomcat service <br /> / Usr / local / tomcat / bin / catalina.sh start <br /> / Usr / local / apache / bin / apachectl start <br /><br /> 5 Test the cluster <br /><br /> After all of the above steps, a two node cluster has been configured tomcat, but sometimes may not be copied conversation among peers, because all nodes must server.xml in tcpListenAddress = &quot;auto&quot; to tcpListenAddress = &quot; 10.3.15.85 &quot;, that is, to the real ip address. <br /> If activated, the following message appears: skipping state transfer. No members active in cluster group. Also need to modify the above information. Otherwise, session is not replicated between multiple tomcat\'s session. <br /><br /> 5.1 Write a simple web application, including the following: <br /> Write a the following two jsp pages. <br /> test.jsp as follows: <br /> &lt;% @ Page contentType = &quot;text / html; charset = GBK&quot;%&gt; <br /> &lt;% @ Page import = &quot;com.WorkerBean&quot;%&gt; <br /> &lt;% @ Page import = &quot;java.net .*&quot;%&gt; <br /> &lt;html&gt; <br /> &lt;head&gt; <br /> &lt;title&gt; <br /> test <br /> &lt;/ Title&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Head&gt; <br /><br /> &lt;body bgcolor=&quot;#ffffff&quot;&gt; <br /> &lt;% = Request.getSession (). GetId ()%&gt; <br /><br /> &lt;% <br /> int i = 0; <br /> WorkerBean test = new WorkerBean (); <br /> / / HttpSession tsession = request.getSession (); <br /> test.setWorker_no (request.getSession (). getId () + i); <br /> session.setAttribute (&quot;worker_no&quot;, test.getWorker_no ()); <br /><br /> System.out.println (&quot;OK&quot;); <br /> System.out.println (&quot;session.getAttribute ()==&quot;+ session.getAttribute (&quot; worker_no &quot;)); <br /> out.println (&quot;session.getAttribute ()==&quot;+ session.getAttribute (&quot; worker_no &quot;)); out.println (&quot; OK &quot;); <br /><br /> %&gt; <br /> &lt;a href=&quot;testResult.jsp&quot;&gt; testResult.jsp &lt;/ a&gt; <br /> &lt;h1&gt; Tomcat &lt;/ h1&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Body&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Html&gt; <br /><br /> testResult.jsp as follows <br /> &lt;% @ Page contentType = &quot;text / html; charset = GBK&quot;%&gt; <br /> &lt;% @ Page import = &quot;com.WorkerBean&quot;%&gt; <br /> &lt;% @ Page import = &quot;java.net .*&quot;%&gt; <br /> &lt;html&gt; <br /> &lt;head&gt; <br /> &lt;title&gt; <br /> test <br /> &lt;/ Title&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Head&gt; <br /><br /> &lt;body bgcolor=&quot;#ffffff&quot;&gt; <br /><br /> &lt;% <br /><br /> System.out.println (&quot;OK&quot;); <br /> System.out.println (&quot;session.getAttribute ()==&quot;+ session.getAttribute (&quot; worker_no &quot;)); <br /> out.println (&quot;OK&quot;); out.println (&quot;session.getAttribute ()==&quot;+ session.getAttribute (&quot; worker_no &quot;)); <br /> %&gt; <br /> &lt;h1&gt; Tomcat &lt;/ h1&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Body&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Html&gt; <br /><br /><br /> 5.2 The preparation of the jsp call javaBean class. <br /><br /> WorkerBean.java <br /> public class WorkerBean implements java.io.Serializable { <br /> String worker_no; <br /><br /> / ** <br /> Ã¯ÂÂ¬ @ return Returns worker_no. <br /> * / <br /> public String getWorker_no () { <br /> return worker_no; <br /> } <br /><br /> / ** <br /> Ã¯ÂÂ¬ @ param worker_no to setThe worker_no. <br /> * / <br /> public void setWorker_no (String worker_no) { <br /> this.worker_no = worker_no; <br /> } <br /><br /> } <br /><br /> Note: This class must implement serialization, object to the existence of this class session, session is to copy in the cluster, or session object can not be replicated in the cluster. <br /> 5.3 configuring web.xml file NOTE: Be sure to add &lt;distributable/&gt;, and other common application is the same. <br /> &lt;? Xml version = &quot;1.0&quot; encoding = &quot;UTF-8&quot;?&gt; <br /> &lt;! DOCTYPE web-app PUBLIC &quot;- / / Sun Microsystems, Inc. / / DTD Web Application 2.3 / / EN&quot; &quot;http://java.sun.com/dtd/web-app_2_3.dtd&quot;&gt; <br /> &lt;web-app&gt; <br /> &lt;display-name&gt; web &lt;/ display-name&gt; <br /> &lt;distributable/&gt; <br /> &lt;/ Web-app&gt; <br /> 5.4 ensure that the server.xml as shown in Appendix 1 and Appendix 2: slightly <br /> 5.5 publish web applications, to test all of the above files to tomcat\'s webapps / ROOT directory, overwrite the original file on it. <br /> 5.6 web application testing and start apache and tomcat1 tomcat2. <br /> In the browser address bar http://10.3.15.85/ will see the following page <br /><br /> In the browser address bar http://10.3.15.85/test.jsp will see the following page <br /><br /> Click above to page 2.jsp connection, enter the following page <br /><br /><br /><br /> The output of the console can be found with the watch, 2 turns of the response to the request tomcat. <br /> Then, any one of them off tomcat, and then click 2.jsp, or can be responsive. Note the cluster automatically take over the application of machine error and found the value of which is the same session, that session in the cluster between the different tomcat session replication. <br /><br /> Summary: Through the above tests and other tools of the test and found that if two machines for tomcat cluster, tomcat more than one individual may support more concurrent, and can do a wrong, the other automatically takes over. 2 sets of separate but no support was complicated by multiple tomcat. </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' Configuration before the application of preparatory work before the cluster in the configuration of the cluster configuration information has a good design, the following is the configuration of our cluster information:  Different machines on the same network segment configured on the cluster, the...'),(169,'Cluster Technology','Load_Balancing','en','/a/lb/2010/0520/106.html','http://www.ixdba.net','Here we have four components: ...','Here_we_have_four_components_','2010-05-20','0000-00-00 00:00:00','script><table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p align=\"left\" class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: left; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan\"> <span style=