nto the IPMI LAN, directly RHAS4. 4 comes with the IPMI service will be able to drive up, and can work, 2 Ethernet ports IPMI machine directly connected, but if there is a machine completely unplug the power, then switching will have problems, it is estimated RHCS a problem, because only in the fence command preparation unit must wait until after a successful return to take over the service, but the host power line of regard, and there can be no recovery, and results available to the machine will always show fence failed, and not to take over the service, which is not a BUG RHCS it? </p><p> hqonline </p><p> As far as I understand, fence device as follows from the role that, when an accident causes the service to stop or when the host machine, LINUX in order to ensure data integrity, reboot the host before the service, issued by the heavy equipment machine signals from the machine , the host machine restarts, the process, prepare the opportunity to take over services. fence device is the signal sent from the heavy equipment. </p><p> aquaofchina </p><p> I was assigned an implementation using HP-iLO, feeling that in order to ensure exclusive shared disk, and only wait to receive the fault signal to restart the machine has started, prepare machine began to take over the service. Is the first machine malfunction sends a reboot signal iLO port and start the machine periodically iLO from the failure to take the machine state until taken to the state DOWN. </p><p><br /> ibm pc server + rhas4.4 + rhcs4.4 configuration method of fence <br /> hqonline </p><p> This post is to answer simonocn problems, while for everyone to share what <br /> ibm pc server + rhas4.4 + rhcs4.4 configuration fence the following ways: <br /> Hardware: <br /> 1, 2, server, configured in the BIOS, BMC\'s IP address, such as 192.168.10.100, the same two machines <br /> 2, 1 to 2 machine network port to link with a direct connection, or connected to the same switch or in the same VLAN, <br /> Software: <br /> 1, 2, server, configure the system in a corresponding network interface card (ethx), the IP address assigned to 192.168.10.101 and 192.168.10.102, two machines can not be the same, and then have to pass ping to see what 192.168.10.100 on OK, <br /> 2, IPMI service in the service will start, with <br /> service ipmi start <br /> Set to boot from the start <br /> chkconfig ipmi on <br /> 3, set the fence device in the cluster when <br /> IPMI option <br /> Name: bmc (played casually, whatever) <br /> Address input: 192.168.10.100 <br /> User Name: USERID <br /> Password: PASSW0RD (Note that the default is PASSWORD to \'O\' into \'0 \', if changed to fill out their own) <br /> Authentication: blank, blank on the line so that you can, the other based on how CLUSTER how to set it finally note that the test can not pull the power test, which does not support internal fence device pulling power test. Unplug the power back on because the machine can not communicate a host, cluster will not work, even if the plug will not work again. Cluster can only restart the service. </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' In the linux-ha project, has become increasingly concerned about the io fence devices.  Ha and in rhes4 also supported in more io fence devices.  1. Why use io fence devices: the way simply because the software does not provide the full sense of HA. So the need for additional hardware to be...'),(172,'Cluster Technology','Load_Balancing','en','/a/lb/2010/0421/1.html','http://www.ixdba.net',' Learning linux, you may...','_Learning_linux_you_may','2010-04-21','0000-00-00 00:00:00','<table width=\"100%\"><tr><td><p> Learning linux, you may encounter problems linux cluster here will introduce the method of <font style=\"background-color: #ffffff\">load balancing</font> linux cluster, after careful finishing, out here and share with you, I hope this will teach you more. </p><p> <strong>Cluster theory</strong> <br /> linux cluster nodes and cluster system consists of two parts, the cluster manager. Sometimes referred to as node cluster nodes, servers, or server node is to provide the processing resources of the system, which carried out the actual work of the cluster. In general, it must be configured in order to become part of the cluster, the cluster must run the application software. Applications can be dedicated to the cluster software can also be designed for distributed systems with standard software. node linux cluster manager sucked bundled together to form the logical structure of the appearance of a single system, which is used to break down tasks to all nodes. </p><p> Cluster due to a variety of different types have different reasons to establish the most direct reason linux cluster is a shared CPU resources, balance the load between multiple machines, more reliability, or failure to provide the host backup system (switch). </p><p> Through the analysis of related software, to achieve the function of the cluster load is achieved through traffic management, specifically the following approaches: direct routing (Direct Forwarding), Network Address Translation (NAT) and tunneling (Tunneling). </p><p> Direct routing (Direct Forwarding) is that when participating in the cluster control and management computer and the computer as a segment in the same time make this method. Control and management of the computer receives the request packet, directly to the participating cluster nodes. The advantage is that the flow is not returned to the client through the control unit, speed, cost less. </p><p> Perhaps we are all familiar with Network Address Translation (NAT) this approach. Address converter has access to the outside world can be a legitimate IP address, it changes the outflow from the private network address of the package, the outside world looks from the address converter package itself. When the external packet to the converter, it should determine which packets to the internal network nodes. Its advantage is to save IP addresses can be disguised within; disadvantage is low efficiency, because the flow is returned to the requesting party to go through a converter. </p><p> Tunneling (Tunneling) linux cluster in this way the nodes are not in the same segment of the forwarding mechanism used, the IP packet is encapsulated in the other network traffic. From a security point of view, technology should be used in the tunnel VPN, leased lines can also be used. </p><p> linux cluster can provide the service is based on TCP / IP, Web Services, Mail Services, News Services, DNS Services and Proxy servers. Here I will take a specific product TurboLinux Cluster Server to implement a load balancing linux cluster system, used to provide Web and FTP services. </p><p> <strong>Planning <br /></strong> 1. Providing services: Web, FTP. <br /> 2. Do a better load balancing system to which more features can be used to. <br /> 3. With 4 servers, 3 sets to install TurboLinux Cluster Server, 1 station to install Windows 2000 Sever. </p><p> <strong>Installation</strong> <br /> 1. In the 3 servers installed Turbo Linux, also need to install Apache and wu-ftpd, because the linux cluster to provide this service. After installation is complete, restart the machine, mount CD-ROM in the directory / mnt / cdrom, execute. / TLCS-install, then follow the prompts to complete installation. <br /> 2. In a single server installation of Windows 2000 Server, also install Internet Information Server 5.0. </p><p> <strong>Linux cluster manager configuration <br /></strong> 1. To set the server\'s IP address, subnet mask, routing, etc., transferred through the network, and a table set TurboLinux Server DNS server to be able to resolve forward and reverse resolution. In this case the server is named pc1, domain test.com. <br /> 2. Configure Cluster Server. Executive Turbolinuxclusteradmin, set as follows (hyphen connected to the lower menu or menu option, set the case after the colon): <br /> (1) ClusterServer Configuration-Cluster Services-Application Stability Agents: <br /> Ã¢Â—Â† http as the default service, do not set. <br /> Ã¢Â—Â† ftp:/usr/lib/ftpAgent. <br /> (2) ClusterServer Configuration - Cluster Services - Service Settings: <br /> Ã¢Â—Â† http, 80: TCP, sticky. <br /> Ã¢Â—Â† ftp, 21: TCP, ftp. <br /> (3) ClusterServer Configuration - Servers Configuration: <br /> Ã¢Â—Â† pc1 (pc1.test.com), direct, ping. <br /> Ã¢Â—Â† pc2 (pc2.test.com), direct, ping. <br /> Ã¢Â—Â† pc3 (pc3.test.com), direct, ping. <br /> Ã¢Â—Â† pc4 (pc4.test.com), direct, ping. <br /> (4) ClusterServer Configuration - Advance Traffic Managers: <br /> Ã¢Â—Â† Advance Traffic Manager System: pc1.test.com. <br /> Ã¢Â—Â† Advance Traffic Manager Setting: The default value. <br /> (5) ClusterServer ConfigurationÃƒÂ Virtual Severs: <br /> Ã¢Â—Â† host: pc1.test.com. <br /> Ã¢Â—Â† sendmail: master @ pc1. Test.com. <br /> Ã¢Â—Â† Server pool name: Server Group1. <br /> (6) ClusterServer ConfigurationÃƒÂ Globle Settings: <br /> Network settings: netmask 255.255.255.0. </p><p> <strong>Each node in the cluster configuration <br /></strong> 1. Configuring Windows 2000 Server node as TurboLinux Cluster Server tool itself can be automatically synchronized, so long as you can configure Windows 2000 Server. <br /> (1) Start Ã¢Â†Â’ Settings Ã¢Â†Â’ Control Panel Ã¢Â†Â’ Add New Hardware Ã¢Â†Â’ Next Ã¢Â†Â’ Add / Troubleshoot a device to add new equipment Ã¢Â†Â’ Ã¢Â†Â’ not, then select from a list of other equipment, hardware Ã¢Â†Â’ Ã¢Â†Â’ Microsoft: Microsoft Loopback Adapter Ã¢Â†Â’ completed. <br /> (2) Right-click the desktop select My Network Places Ã¢Â†Â’ Properties Ã¢Â†Â’ TCP / IP, set the IP address, default gateway, subnet mask (the first set to 255.255.255.0). <br /> (3) Start Ã¢Â†Â’ Run Ã¢Â†Â’ regedit Ã¢Â†Â’ find the registry with the Microsoft Loopback Adapter-related items, change the subnet mask 255.255.255.255. <br /> (4) configure the system to run the appropriate services, and configuration management for the cluster manager configuration so that we can use the Control Manager. </p><p> 2. Configuration TurboLinux Cluster Server Node (1) in the management of the implementation of the contents of the menu select tlcs_content _sync synchronization, enter the password to configure the node, the cluster manager will copy the content to the service node. <br /> (2) in the management menu, select Settings tlcs_ config _sync perform synchronization, enter the password to be configured node, copy the settings in the cluster manager to the node content. <br /> At this point we can already see that the cluster manager running on PC1, the client can access servers connected to the switch, the client can request Web and FTP services. If you want to see the operation can also be used from the Cluster Manager console https: / / pc1.test.com: 910 to manage. </p><p> In computer technology, cluster load balancing is a hot technology, but also a high-end applications. Internet / Intranet solutions using a wide range of load-balancing cluster, especially in medium to large sites is immune from this technology. Direct routing, Network Address Translation, tunneling technology will be used according to application needs. </p> (Editor: South African Ant) </td></tr></table>',' Learning linux, you may encounter problems linux cluster here will introduce the method of load balancing linux cluster, after careful finishing, out here and share with you, I hope this will teach you more. Cluster theory linux cluster nodes and cluster system consists of two parts, the cluster...');
